1
00:01:15,291 --> 00:01:17,500
There once lived a king,
whose mighty empire spanned

2
00:01:17,541 --> 00:01:19,875
from Moodanagudda and lasted
till the Paduvana sea.

3
00:01:20,166 --> 00:01:23,958
A caring wife and children
to call as his own.

4
00:01:24,541 --> 00:01:27,375
Loyal subjects to whom
their king meant everything.

5
00:01:27,375 --> 00:01:29,541
A royal figure who was
friendly with one and all.

6
00:01:29,583 --> 00:01:33,333
He had everything,
except for peace of mind.

7
00:01:34,250 --> 00:01:37,583
He visited numerous temples and
took a dip in many holy ponds.

8
00:01:37,791 --> 00:01:41,375
Despite performing various religious
rituals and worshipping his ancestors,

9
00:01:41,666 --> 00:01:45,166
Sound sleep and peace
of mind evaded the King.

10
00:01:45,208 --> 00:01:46,291
But why?

11
00:01:46,291 --> 00:01:48,375
With that very question in
mind, the king consulted

12
00:01:48,375 --> 00:01:50,333
a soothsayer seeking
answers to his predicament.

13
00:01:50,375 --> 00:01:52,333
O' King, you possess everything.

14
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:56,375
However, until you find a source of strength
that will guide you like a wise uncle

15
00:01:56,416 --> 00:02:00,291
unconditionally love you like a
mother, you shall not attain peace.

16
00:02:00,666 --> 00:02:02,250
Where would I find it, Sir?

17
00:02:02,250 --> 00:02:03,291
Go in search of it.

18
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:04,333
All alone.

19
00:02:06,708 --> 00:02:07,875
The king then set off.

20
00:02:09,625 --> 00:02:13,000
He visits various pilgrimage centres,
meets all kinds of spiritual guides.

21
00:02:13,583 --> 00:02:17,125
But no matter where he went,
the pain in his heart found no solace.

22
00:02:17,958 --> 00:02:25,208
Assuming that there was no place or power that could
give him peace, the King went to the forests.

23
00:02:26,083 --> 00:02:31,125
Right in the middle of the woods,
he heard the distant sound of an anklet.

24
00:02:32,041 --> 00:02:34,125
The king halted right there.

25
00:02:34,583 --> 00:02:37,333
But surprisingly,
the sound doesn't frighten the King.

26
00:02:37,708 --> 00:02:41,291
It reminded him of a mother’s
love and an uncle’s affection.

27
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:44,333
The king then moved in the
direction of the sound.

28
00:02:45,083 --> 00:02:49,583
He is guided towards a stone, in front
of which, he surrenders his weapon.

29
00:02:52,083 --> 00:02:56,291
Without the King's knowledge, his eyes teared
up and his hands joined together in reverence.

30
00:02:56,458 --> 00:02:57,875
The king felt joy.

31
00:02:57,916 --> 00:02:59,833
Infinite joy that had
evaded him all this while.

32
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:01,625
Like a mother hugged him.

33
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:03,291
Like an uncle caressed his head.

34
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:04,500
Right then...

35
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:13,875
I bow down as your king.

36
00:03:14,666 --> 00:03:16,375
Please bestow this
Demigod to me.

37
00:03:17,083 --> 00:03:19,125
I’m ready to give
you anything for it.

38
00:03:21,041 --> 00:03:22,083
My dear King!

39
00:03:22,458 --> 00:03:26,291
Ask us for anything,
but not our Demigod Panjurli.

40
00:03:41,875 --> 00:03:46,791
So, you want me,
the Panjurli Demigod, huh?

41
00:03:46,791 --> 00:03:48,791
I want nothing but you, Panjurli.

42
00:03:49,041 --> 00:03:50,500
I shall come along with you.

43
00:03:50,541 --> 00:03:52,458
But I belong to this village.

44
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:57,708
If I bestow you with happiness, peace and
prosperity, what will you give my people?

45
00:03:58,375 --> 00:03:59,750
Whatever you ask for.

46
00:04:06,041 --> 00:04:10,916
You will grant all of the land, across
which the sound of my voice traversed.

47
00:04:13,041 --> 00:04:16,916
Remember, I'll be accompanied by my
Compatriot spirit, the ferocious Guliga.

48
00:04:17,666 --> 00:04:23,250
Should you err, even if I forgive
you, Kshetrapala Guliga won't.

49
00:04:27,125 --> 00:04:28,333
You have my word, Panjurli.

50
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,625
The palace is decorated and
the village is spruced up.

51
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:43,458
The King welcomed the Demigod with
inexplicable joy into his kingdom.

52
00:04:44,041 --> 00:04:47,875
Since then, the King's life saw no
dearth in harmony, joy and peace.

53
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,333
The villagers' Demigod was
now in the lap of the King.

54
00:04:56,375 --> 00:04:58,875
The King’s vast land was now
in the hands of the villagers.

55
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:07,000
From then on, the holy procession
commenced from the King’s palace.

56
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:10,625
Then why is the current Landlord
asking us to return this land?

57
00:05:10,666 --> 00:05:12,208
After all this is their
land, son!

58
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:14,291
There is nothing wrong if
they ask us to return it.

59
00:05:14,291 --> 00:05:16,541
But we're here to serve the
Demigods, aren't we?

60
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:19,208
Where can we go
forsaking our Gods?

61
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:21,583
Son, do you know where
we humans go wrong?

62
00:05:21,666 --> 00:05:23,625
We assume that we own
everything around us.

63
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:25,916
But forget the reality of
the true owner of it all.

64
00:05:25,916 --> 00:05:28,291
Once we become aware of the
truth, we can live peacefully.

65
00:05:36,625 --> 00:05:39,541
I didn't come all the way from Bombay
to watch Bhootha Kola [SPIRIT WORSHIP].

66
00:05:39,583 --> 00:05:41,375
I need to settle this
land issue on priority.

67
00:05:41,416 --> 00:05:43,000
Do you even hear yourself?

68
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:46,458
This land was donated by our
ancestors to serve the Demigod.

69
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,958
Since then, our family has
been living peacefully.

70
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,083
That's enough!

71
00:05:50,458 --> 00:05:51,916
Wasn't it given as charity back then?

72
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:54,708
Do you have the slightest
idea about its current value?

73
00:05:55,375 --> 00:05:57,833
If we take it back now,
we can lead a life with dignity.

74
00:05:57,875 --> 00:05:59,125
It doesn't work that way.

75
00:05:59,416 --> 00:06:02,625
Asking for the land back would mean going
back on the word given to the Demigod.

76
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:04,625
You and your Demigod
can take a hike!

77
00:06:04,875 --> 00:06:06,833
I'm sick of hearing
this all the time.

78
00:06:07,208 --> 00:06:10,375
The performance you'll see is something
I've witnessed many times before.

79
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:13,541
This is our ancestral property.

80
00:06:14,125 --> 00:06:16,000
I have as much right
over it as you do.

81
00:06:16,291 --> 00:06:18,250
If you can't ask for it,
then take a step back,

82
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:20,583
I'll handle this in court.

83
00:06:46,208 --> 00:06:51,041
I present you the sacred offering
and invite you to wear the gaggara.

84
00:06:51,291 --> 00:06:56,375
I humbly accept your invite and seek the
permission of audiences to wear gaggara.

85
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:07,125
♪ Varaha,
the Supreme among all Gods ♪

86
00:07:07,166 --> 00:07:13,291
♪ Varaha,
the Supreme among all Gods ♪

87
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:15,875
♪ He who assumes the form of a Wild boar ♪

88
00:07:15,916 --> 00:07:18,708
♪ The greatest of the Demons ♪

89
00:07:19,166 --> 00:07:22,916
♪ With teeth as
hard as Diamond ♪

90
00:07:22,958 --> 00:07:26,833
♪ He who protects
us like a shield ♪

91
00:07:36,916 --> 00:07:39,916
♪ He who embodies the
essence of Shiva ♪

92
00:07:39,958 --> 00:07:42,625
♪ The one who thrives on Earth ♪

93
00:07:42,916 --> 00:07:48,750
♪ He who gives refuge to
those who believe in him ♪

94
00:07:48,791 --> 00:07:54,875
♪ The one who has won the
hearts of Thousands of Gods ♪

95
00:07:54,916 --> 00:08:02,916
♪ We now stand in front of
you, worshipping you ♪

96
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:45,833
O' Landlord!

97
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:49,208
It's the twilight hour, O' Landlord!

98
00:08:49,666 --> 00:08:52,375
It's a practice to address
your questions in my court.

99
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:55,458
Do you have any
questions, Landlord?

100
00:08:55,541 --> 00:08:57,500
Panjurli?
- Yes!

101
00:08:58,041 --> 00:09:00,625
As of now, I have no questions.

102
00:09:00,625 --> 00:09:01,666
I do.

103
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:02,791
What?!

104
00:09:05,791 --> 00:09:07,625
This place, this
property, this land.

105
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:09,291
None of these belong
to the villagers.

106
00:09:09,291 --> 00:09:11,625
Quiet. Don't talk, please.
- Fine! It's not yours either.

107
00:09:11,625 --> 00:09:12,750
It's mine.

108
00:09:13,625 --> 00:09:15,250
You have to ensure
it's returned to me.

109
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:18,708
That's a great question, Landlord!

110
00:09:19,583 --> 00:09:21,250
I'll ensure it's
returned to you.

111
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:23,416
I'll ensure the villagers'
land is returned to you!

112
00:09:25,875 --> 00:09:29,541
But can you return the peace I have
blessed you with all these years?

113
00:09:29,583 --> 00:09:32,375
Listen!
Won't you be able to get it back for me?

114
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,958
No problem.
I know where to get my job done.

115
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:39,750
So, you will go to the Court, eh?

116
00:09:41,041 --> 00:09:44,208
But I shall pronounce your
judgment on those very stairs.

117
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,375
The land belongs
to the villagers.

118
00:09:46,958 --> 00:09:48,583
That decision will
not be made today.

119
00:09:48,625 --> 00:09:50,583
A day will come in
the distant future.

120
00:09:50,583 --> 00:09:51,916
It belongs to the villagers?

121
00:09:52,541 --> 00:09:55,833
Is this the Demigod speaking?
Or is it the performer?

122
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:10,375
Is it the Demigod or the performer?
Let it be decided today.

123
00:10:11,583 --> 00:10:14,958
If it indeed is the performer,
may you find me again.

124
00:10:15,208 --> 00:10:16,625
However, if it is the Demigod...

125
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:29,875
Shiva!

126
00:10:48,916 --> 00:10:55,583
KANTARA - A LEGEND

127
00:11:04,625 --> 00:11:05,833
Did he really disappear?

128
00:11:05,875 --> 00:11:06,875
Of course he did.

129
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:08,708
Wouldn't he have
returned otherwise?

130
00:11:08,708 --> 00:11:10,000
What if he was killed?

131
00:11:10,125 --> 00:11:11,708
If so,
wouldn't we have found his body?

132
00:11:11,833 --> 00:11:12,958
That's right.

133
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:15,250
Do you want to see the
place where he went missing?

134
00:11:15,291 --> 00:11:18,125
In the forest, a fire was ablaze
across the place he went missing in.

135
00:11:18,375 --> 00:11:22,041
But the fire didn't illuminate the forest,
instead it pushed it into further darkness.

136
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:23,458
What about the Landlord?

137
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:26,291
He died vomiting blood on
the stairs of the court.

138
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:28,000
An extremely powerful Demigod.
- Of course.

139
00:11:28,208 --> 00:11:31,375
But I shall pronounce your
judgment on those very stairs.

140
00:11:42,625 --> 00:11:45,125
What a powerful Demigod!
- Of course.

141
00:11:45,625 --> 00:11:48,875
Even today, the Demigod protects this
forest, the village and its people.

142
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:50,708
So damn powerful!

143
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:59,958
[SONG HERALDING THE COMMENCEMENT OF
KAMBALA - A TRADITIONAL BUFFALO RACE]

144
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:33,833
[WARM WELCOME TO GUDDI SUDHAKARA,
A RAY OF HOPE TO THE POOR]

145
00:12:35,166 --> 00:12:36,625
Which idiot drew this?

146
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:37,708
No clue.

147
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:39,250
If you find out,
ask him to meet me.

148
00:12:41,291 --> 00:12:42,291
Give me the garland!

149
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:43,750
The Landlord is here!

150
00:12:45,625 --> 00:12:48,083
The chief guest of today's Kambala
festival, Devendra Suttur is here...

151
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:50,208
These garlands were
meant for the buffaloes!

152
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:54,833
Is that the Landlord?
- Yep.

153
00:12:54,875 --> 00:12:56,833
Is he the son of the guy who
died vomiting blood?

154
00:12:56,875 --> 00:12:58,333
Yes.
- Is he also like his father?

155
00:12:58,333 --> 00:13:00,166
Not at all.
He has a heart of gold.

156
00:13:00,208 --> 00:13:02,791
Get ice candy for the kids.
- What is the matter with his child?

157
00:13:02,958 --> 00:13:04,125
No point talking about it.

158
00:13:04,791 --> 00:13:05,916
Let’s proceed Landlord.

159
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,041
Since the Suttur's ancestors
are our royal family.

160
00:13:08,083 --> 00:13:09,333
[LUCKY DIP - 1ST PRIZE MOTOR BIKE]

161
00:13:09,375 --> 00:13:12,916
Could one get this bike for real?
- The winner surely can.

162
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:20,875
On behalf of Keradi family, we request
you to make this event a grand success.

163
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:24,208
Keradi Kambala has been a
prestigious race with...

164
00:13:24,208 --> 00:13:25,958
Hope everything is ready.
- Yes it's done.

165
00:13:25,958 --> 00:13:27,333
Hey look! Your wife!

166
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:29,041
Check out her glances!

167
00:13:30,166 --> 00:13:32,041
Check out this Buffalo's teeth.

168
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:35,458
One look and you know
it's an experienced one.

169
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:37,958
Hello, Mr Sudhakar Shetty!
- Go on, Mr Rajiv Shetty!

170
00:13:37,958 --> 00:13:40,541
Shall we call the buffaloes into the arena?
- Definitely.

171
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,625
Will the Kola continue?
- Why won't it?

172
00:13:42,666 --> 00:13:44,083
So, who's performing?

173
00:13:44,125 --> 00:13:46,166
As per tradition,
Shiva must be the one to perform.

174
00:13:46,208 --> 00:13:47,791
He's an irresponsible fellow.

175
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:50,250
So, his cousin Guruva
will be performing.

176
00:13:51,083 --> 00:13:52,500
Come for the Kola.
Don’t miss it.

177
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:55,333
Bring your wife, too.
We'll have a blast.

178
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:57,166
The owners of all
buffaloes please proceed...

179
00:13:57,166 --> 00:14:00,791
Yes, I was sitting with your wife.
Hit me!

180
00:14:02,375 --> 00:14:03,833
Rampa come! It’s getting late.

181
00:14:03,875 --> 00:14:07,583
We are now witnessing Kaadubettu
Shivannaʼs buffaloes entering the field.

182
00:14:11,625 --> 00:14:14,416
FORGE AHEAD!

183
00:14:14,958 --> 00:14:16,458
Let’s charge!

184
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:48,625
That was awesome, Shiva!

185
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:52,583
Shiva, you beat your previous
record by two seconds!

186
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,291
That was splendid racing!

187
00:14:57,041 --> 00:14:59,000
Will our buffalo win
at least this time?

188
00:14:59,083 --> 00:15:02,000
Just win?
It will break all records!

189
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,833
Just wait and watch Landlord!

190
00:15:04,208 --> 00:15:05,500
It doesn’t matter who wins.

191
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:07,000
They are our people after all!

192
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,625
Run!

193
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:22,041
Superb! Our buffaloes made it first!

194
00:15:22,083 --> 00:15:27,166
[KUNDAPURA FOLKLORE]

195
00:15:37,208 --> 00:15:39,166
Shiva, slow down. I’m tired.

196
00:15:39,166 --> 00:15:41,458
Tired? Did you run the race?
- Give me the booze.

197
00:15:42,291 --> 00:15:43,666
Pour it.
- It’s hot.

198
00:15:43,791 --> 00:15:45,875
Give it I say.
I'm the one drinking.

199
00:16:20,916 --> 00:16:22,791
I’m leaving.
- Already?

200
00:16:23,708 --> 00:16:24,916
Mahadevanna, give me a drag.

201
00:16:24,916 --> 00:16:26,750
Man, our buffaloes ran
like there's no tomorrow!

202
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,500
The buffaloes are running.

203
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:34,416
The buffaloes are running
with all their might.

204
00:16:35,833 --> 00:16:41,083
But ironically,
the owner ends up getting the medal.

205
00:16:42,791 --> 00:16:44,375
Bet 10 bucks and take home 20!

206
00:16:44,416 --> 00:16:46,666
Bet 10 bucks on
Tiger Prabhakar now!

207
00:16:47,250 --> 00:16:49,625
I bet 10 bucks on Tiger Prabhakar.
- I bet on Silk Smitha.

208
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,250
Yay! Give me the prize!

209
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:56,208
I won.

210
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:57,875
Move aside.

211
00:16:57,875 --> 00:17:00,750
Shivanna, the Landlord’s buffaloes
finished six seconds later than ours.

212
00:17:02,916 --> 00:17:03,916
Let’s go.

213
00:17:04,125 --> 00:17:06,041
Wait.
I’ll bet on Silk Smitha again.

214
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:07,375
You won’t get her, come.

215
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:11,708
Congratulations!

216
00:17:12,958 --> 00:17:14,083
Lucky you!

217
00:17:14,708 --> 00:17:16,916
Shivanna,
I don’t know how to ride a bike.

218
00:17:18,041 --> 00:17:25,250
On behalf of the Keradi ancestral house, we thank all
the 50 buffalo owners who participated in the event.

219
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:31,375
The third place in today's Kambala
race goes to Thumbebailu Mahesh.

220
00:17:32,416 --> 00:17:33,458
He bagged it!

221
00:17:33,458 --> 00:17:35,666
The second place goes to….

222
00:17:35,708 --> 00:17:36,833
Kaadabettu's...

223
00:17:39,375 --> 00:17:40,625
Shivanna's buffaloes.

224
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:42,833
What?

225
00:17:43,375 --> 00:17:47,916
The first place in today's Kambala race
goes to Devendra Suttur’s buffaloes.

226
00:17:48,291 --> 00:17:49,833
Oh finally!
Our Landlord won!

227
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:53,250
Which bas*ard said so?!
- Shiva!

228
00:17:53,250 --> 00:17:55,333
If rookies turn into judge,
this is what happens!

229
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:57,708
I’ll break your leg moron!
How did he win?

230
00:17:57,708 --> 00:17:59,125
You stay out of this!

231
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:00,875
I’m a big man in this village!

232
00:18:00,916 --> 00:18:03,708
You think you’re the prince of
Barkur, dingbat?!

233
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:06,166
How did his buffaloes win?
- They ran. So they won. How else?!

234
00:18:06,208 --> 00:18:08,500
Is the Landlord your father to award him?!
- Moron!

235
00:18:08,541 --> 00:18:10,291
Dimwit, you’re the moron!

236
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:11,708
I’ll kill you scoundrel!

237
00:18:16,625 --> 00:18:19,125
Is your father
judging this contest?

238
00:18:19,166 --> 00:18:20,166
You slob!

239
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:24,000
You guys are destroying the
reputation of the Kambala.

240
00:18:24,166 --> 00:18:25,291
You bash him, Shiva!

241
00:18:27,083 --> 00:18:28,916
Come here, you Landlord’s dog!

242
00:18:34,666 --> 00:18:36,791
Handle the mic with care.
It’s not your father’s!

243
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:38,291
Don’t you dare talk
about my father!

244
00:18:38,333 --> 00:18:39,875
Landlord!

245
00:18:56,083 --> 00:18:57,500
Smash him!

246
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:13,000
Wow! Shiva's smashing them!

247
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,458
Don't you see him
getting beaten up?

248
00:19:15,166 --> 00:19:17,125
Whose side are you on?
- I’m on the winner’s side.

249
00:19:18,666 --> 00:19:19,791
Go and thrash him!

250
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:30,875
Thrash him!

251
00:19:38,291 --> 00:19:39,458
God! He's coming here!

252
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:20,916
I’m dead meat!

253
00:20:21,375 --> 00:20:22,541
You wretched dog!

254
00:20:22,916 --> 00:20:24,291
Let’s clean ourselves
at the pond.

255
00:20:24,291 --> 00:20:26,041
The mud has entered the
unmentionable places.

256
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:27,750
Scoundrel!

257
00:20:27,791 --> 00:20:30,791
When the village is together celebrating,
how dare you guys fight instead?

258
00:20:30,833 --> 00:20:31,833
You wretched dog!

259
00:20:32,125 --> 00:20:35,625
He started it all.
How can I keep quiet?

260
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:37,041
So? You guys just fight?

261
00:20:37,041 --> 00:20:39,208
His buffaloes have been winning
for the last three years.

262
00:20:39,208 --> 00:20:41,041
Heʼs one of us.
So letʼs support him.

263
00:20:41,083 --> 00:20:42,791
Go bring the medal.

264
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:45,500
Dammit!

265
00:20:46,291 --> 00:20:47,916
Could it be scotch?
- No clue.

266
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,416
Hey Shiva.
- Landlord?

267
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:52,750
If you’re pissed with me,
vent it out in front of me.

268
00:20:52,791 --> 00:20:54,541
No need to do it in
front of the villagers.

269
00:20:54,583 --> 00:20:55,666
Sorry, Landlord.

270
00:20:55,708 --> 00:20:57,250
Things go out of
hand when I'm drunk.

271
00:20:58,583 --> 00:21:00,125
Then I better be
prepared for more.

272
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:02,041
Yes!
Wait! No!

273
00:21:05,125 --> 00:21:07,125
Shiva wins it consecutively
for the fourth time.

274
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,000
God bless!

275
00:21:13,458 --> 00:21:15,000
We are all from
the same village.

276
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,875
We have to live in
harmony till the end.

277
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,666
What do you say?
- You're right.

278
00:21:22,041 --> 00:21:23,375
This is for the
Kola celebrations.

279
00:21:23,375 --> 00:21:24,833
Make sure it’s grand.

280
00:21:24,833 --> 00:21:26,541
Let me know if it doesn't suffice.

281
00:21:28,125 --> 00:21:29,291
Okay then.

282
00:21:29,791 --> 00:21:30,833
What is it?

283
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:32,166
Go on. Take it.

284
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:34,458
Good Lord!
We waited all this while for this!

285
00:21:34,791 --> 00:21:37,000
The Landlord is so fond of
us that he thrashed Mohan!

286
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,958
You should have seen his face!

287
00:21:39,208 --> 00:21:41,333
Guddi looked like the cat that
swallowed the canary!

288
00:21:42,541 --> 00:21:43,916
Hey Mala, Susheela!

289
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:45,541
Where are you off to?

290
00:21:45,541 --> 00:21:46,708
Look at their attitude!

291
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:48,208
Where is your sister?

292
00:21:48,958 --> 00:21:50,333
Look at them making faces!

293
00:21:50,541 --> 00:21:52,833
Hey Rampa,
our Landlord is a good man.

294
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:54,958
He’s the only one who gives
us a party without asking.

295
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,958
Time for some soda!
- One for me too.

296
00:21:57,541 --> 00:21:59,208
What the hell's wrong with you?!

297
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:00,375
Celebrate our victory man!

298
00:22:00,416 --> 00:22:01,583
What rubbish!

299
00:22:02,416 --> 00:22:03,875
Ginger?!
Don’t you have a plain one?

300
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:05,791
That's not it?!
Did I give you the ginger one ?

301
00:22:05,791 --> 00:22:07,291
Yes, damn your ginger!

302
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:09,000
How much is it?
- Don’t worry, it’s on me.

303
00:22:09,041 --> 00:22:10,041
Really?

304
00:22:10,041 --> 00:22:12,416
You take the bike and go to Kailasa.
I’ll join you in a bit.

305
00:22:12,458 --> 00:22:13,541
Hey Abbu! All good?

306
00:22:13,583 --> 00:22:14,583
Yes.

307
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:16,833
Haven’t you gone to the mosque?
- You think I live there?

308
00:22:17,208 --> 00:22:19,500
Shiva is bad company for my
son, Lacchu!

309
00:22:19,541 --> 00:22:20,625
Hey Vasanthi akka (sister)!

310
00:22:20,625 --> 00:22:22,541
Hope he doesn't lose his way.
- Move aside!

311
00:22:22,583 --> 00:22:24,708
Use the horn, monkey!
- Namaskara!

312
00:22:24,750 --> 00:22:27,083
Looks like it's finally yours.
- Could it be anyone else's?

313
00:22:27,083 --> 00:22:28,333
Where is Lacchu?
- What?!

314
00:22:28,375 --> 00:22:30,333
Did he go out hunting?
- Shiva!

315
00:22:31,583 --> 00:22:34,125
Greetings uncle.
- Hey Shiva.

316
00:22:34,166 --> 00:22:36,166
This is the Landlord’s
donation for the Kola.

317
00:22:36,750 --> 00:22:38,125
He wants us to ask
if we need more.

318
00:22:38,125 --> 00:22:40,416
Has there ever been instance
where he hasn’t given enough?

319
00:22:40,458 --> 00:22:42,375
Hey Guruva!
This time too the medal is ours.

320
00:22:42,375 --> 00:22:43,750
Everybody knew that you won.

321
00:22:43,875 --> 00:22:45,083
Did you need this
medal to prove it?

322
00:22:45,125 --> 00:22:47,000
Why should I let go of
what’s rightfully mine?

323
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,916
I need your blessings.
- It’s okay!

324
00:22:49,208 --> 00:22:52,416
Man, he really got Mohana yesterday.
- Real bad.

325
00:22:53,250 --> 00:22:54,250
Kusuma.

326
00:22:55,958 --> 00:22:57,250
You stay here. I’ll come.

327
00:23:01,250 --> 00:23:03,458
Why do you need medicine?
What happened?

328
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:05,416
I saw something last
night and freaked out.

329
00:23:06,125 --> 00:23:07,541
What did you see?
- It was me.

330
00:23:08,083 --> 00:23:10,833
I'm tired of trying to
convince him that it was me.

331
00:23:10,875 --> 00:23:11,875
Well...

332
00:23:11,916 --> 00:23:13,875
I wonder how many more
nightmares await him.

333
00:23:15,750 --> 00:23:16,833
The fighter cock is here.

334
00:23:17,166 --> 00:23:19,750
You called him useless but
he managed to get the medal.

335
00:23:19,791 --> 00:23:21,750
He didn’t get it for the
race, but for wrestling.

336
00:23:21,791 --> 00:23:23,833
He’s the black sheep of his
family and this village.

337
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,000
Hey Kapil and Deva.

338
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,125
There’s only one medal.
Kindly adjust.

339
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:28,250
Where’s mother?

340
00:23:28,625 --> 00:23:29,625
Hasn’t she fed you yet?

341
00:23:29,625 --> 00:23:30,625
It’s right here.

342
00:23:32,041 --> 00:23:33,041
Eat well.

343
00:23:34,291 --> 00:23:36,208
Next year,
we should break this year’s record.

344
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:38,041
If we win, I'll get two medals.

345
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,125
What did you hunt, Lacchu?

346
00:23:40,166 --> 00:23:41,166
A hen.

347
00:23:41,166 --> 00:23:42,916
A hen?
You didn’t have to hunt it.

348
00:23:42,916 --> 00:23:44,416
You could’ve just caught it.

349
00:23:44,458 --> 00:23:47,208
A wild hen dude.
- Where is Rampa?

350
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:49,958
Sire set off in the dawn,
asking me to wait for him.

351
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:53,541
Shivanna, when will you
teach me to ride the bike?

352
00:23:53,583 --> 00:23:55,333
Rampa will train you to ride.

353
00:23:55,375 --> 00:23:56,791
He is out riding right now.

354
00:23:57,333 --> 00:23:58,833
Shall I go and join him?

355
00:23:58,875 --> 00:24:00,541
Don’t interrupt the ride midway.

356
00:24:00,583 --> 00:24:01,875
The bike may jerk to a halt!

357
00:24:05,666 --> 00:24:06,833
This is for Rampa.

358
00:24:07,625 --> 00:24:08,666
This too.

359
00:24:08,875 --> 00:24:10,375
Let’s finish it off
before he comes.

360
00:24:10,791 --> 00:24:11,833
Bulla!

361
00:24:11,958 --> 00:24:13,583
Damn, he’s here!

362
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:16,083
Did you take a shower?
- I didn’t get time.

363
00:24:18,208 --> 00:24:19,541
Mud on your knees?!

364
00:24:19,583 --> 00:24:20,791
Did you fall off the bike?

365
00:24:21,166 --> 00:24:22,166
Well...

366
00:24:22,583 --> 00:24:25,583
I attempted to do this and
something else happened.

367
00:24:27,041 --> 00:24:29,166
Rampanna, I heard you ride well.

368
00:24:29,375 --> 00:24:30,541
I want to ride too.

369
00:24:31,666 --> 00:24:32,666
Shut up and eat.

370
00:24:33,583 --> 00:24:35,583
Hey, this is not boar meat!

371
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:38,583
Guys, shall we go hunting tonight?
- Yes.

372
00:24:42,541 --> 00:24:45,458
Shiva! Where is that dog?

373
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:47,291
Let me get my hands on him!
I’ll thrash him!

374
00:24:48,083 --> 00:24:49,833
Hey! Shivanna!
Where are you off to?

375
00:24:49,875 --> 00:24:51,416
Weren't we going in
the night to hunt?

376
00:24:51,458 --> 00:24:53,125
Then why did he run now?
- No clue.

377
00:24:54,041 --> 00:24:56,083
Bulla, look!

378
00:24:56,125 --> 00:24:57,916
Kamala is walking upside down!

379
00:24:57,916 --> 00:25:00,333
Look at the stick her in hand!
- This one will hurt!

380
00:25:00,333 --> 00:25:03,791
Wastrel!
Look at him hiding in that tree!

381
00:25:03,958 --> 00:25:04,958
Shameless bugger!

382
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,916
Didn’t I tell you not
to hunt wild boars?

383
00:25:06,916 --> 00:25:08,750
You’re fit for roaming
the streets like a dog!

384
00:25:08,791 --> 00:25:10,250
Damn! Who told you we
hunted a wild boar?

385
00:25:10,291 --> 00:25:11,291
It was a wild hen!

386
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:13,833
You shameless liar!

387
00:25:13,875 --> 00:25:16,083
Kamala,
we really hunted a wild hen.

388
00:25:16,125 --> 00:25:17,708
Not a wild boar.
Check if you want.

389
00:25:17,708 --> 00:25:18,958
Dimwit! You stay out of this!

390
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:22,041
Had you gotten married at the right
age, you’d have had kids by now.

391
00:25:22,083 --> 00:25:23,500
Would you have spoilt
them like this?

392
00:25:23,541 --> 00:25:25,708
Despite your age, you have no brains!
Bloody wretch!

393
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:27,750
What can I do if you
got married at 13?

394
00:25:27,875 --> 00:25:29,250
Why are you laughing?

395
00:25:29,291 --> 00:25:31,083
What are you doing
with this old man?

396
00:25:31,125 --> 00:25:33,250
I came to Ramappa to learn to ride!
- Kamala!

397
00:25:33,250 --> 00:25:34,375
What’s the matter with you?

398
00:25:34,416 --> 00:25:35,875
You think you’re a teenager?

399
00:25:35,958 --> 00:25:37,958
Hope you remember we studied
together till Class 3.

400
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:40,000
I have been witnessing
your nonsense ever since.

401
00:25:40,041 --> 00:25:41,958
Kamala, are you high?
What makes you speak like this?

402
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:43,000
You shut your mouth!

403
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,250
You, come home!

404
00:25:44,291 --> 00:25:45,458
Your funeral awaits you!

405
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:47,208
I’m sick of this fellow.

406
00:25:47,208 --> 00:25:49,416
What a crazy woman!
- This is exactly why I quit school!

407
00:25:50,291 --> 00:25:51,833
Let’s cancel tonight’s
hunting plans.

408
00:25:51,833 --> 00:25:53,250
We've to attend
your funeral, right?

409
00:25:53,291 --> 00:25:54,291
Bugger off!

410
00:25:54,291 --> 00:25:56,375
We hunted last night.
Haven't slept a wink.

411
00:25:56,416 --> 00:25:58,500
We decided to offer it
first to you and came by.

412
00:25:58,541 --> 00:26:00,333
Sir, please don’t mind.

413
00:26:00,541 --> 00:26:02,458
It's a small wild boar.

414
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:06,458
Next time, we'll hunt a big one!

415
00:26:07,166 --> 00:26:11,916
Irrespective of its size,
it's our duty to offer you the meat.

416
00:26:13,375 --> 00:26:14,708
The Deputy Forest
Officer is here!

417
00:26:15,916 --> 00:26:18,791
Sir, greetings!
- How are you doing, Raghu?

418
00:26:18,833 --> 00:26:19,833
Doing well sir.

419
00:26:19,958 --> 00:26:21,333
Sir please spare us!

420
00:26:21,541 --> 00:26:22,833
What's that sound?

421
00:26:22,875 --> 00:26:24,416
Sir, some repair work is going on.

422
00:26:26,833 --> 00:26:28,583
Is the forest your
ancestral property?

423
00:26:28,583 --> 00:26:29,958
Will you hunt again?!

424
00:26:29,958 --> 00:26:32,208
Morons! Will you hunt again?

425
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:34,500
Murali!

426
00:26:41,166 --> 00:26:44,625
Are you acting smart because
there is no RFO in this division?

427
00:26:44,958 --> 00:26:47,875
At this rate, they will hunt
all the animals in the forest.

428
00:26:47,916 --> 00:26:48,916
So?

429
00:26:49,208 --> 00:26:53,000
If you torture people in your custody,
they will torture you outside.

430
00:26:53,875 --> 00:26:55,041
This is a sensitive area.

431
00:26:55,625 --> 00:26:58,625
If you don't learn to handle the
people, the road ahead looks tough.

432
00:27:03,791 --> 00:27:06,291
Listen,
I donʼt eat meat on Thursday.

433
00:27:06,833 --> 00:27:07,833
You can go.

434
00:27:09,916 --> 00:27:12,000
So many survey stones
have been moved.

435
00:27:13,166 --> 00:27:15,166
Finish the survey soon
and submit the reports.

436
00:27:15,166 --> 00:27:18,291
There are three villages
left apart from Kaadubettu.

437
00:27:22,208 --> 00:27:24,083
Oy! Who goes there?

438
00:27:25,625 --> 00:27:26,708
Come here.

439
00:27:28,291 --> 00:27:29,291
Whatʼs all this?

440
00:27:31,791 --> 00:27:32,958
I'm asking you. What is this?

441
00:27:33,416 --> 00:27:35,958
Different kinds of produce...
- I know that.

442
00:27:36,833 --> 00:27:39,500
Do you have permission to take
all this from a reserve forest?

443
00:27:39,541 --> 00:27:40,583
What for?

444
00:27:40,583 --> 00:27:43,041
Every year, we take all this from
the forest for the Bhootha Kola.

445
00:27:43,083 --> 00:27:45,291
Donʼt you know itʼs
an offence to do so?

446
00:27:45,333 --> 00:27:47,166
Guys, today letʼs hunt
at least four wild boars.

447
00:27:47,166 --> 00:27:48,625
Why? One is enough.

448
00:27:50,333 --> 00:27:51,916
Letʼs go.
You can burn some calories.

449
00:27:52,125 --> 00:27:53,791
Hey, forest officer! Hide!

450
00:27:56,041 --> 00:27:57,708
Take the guns and come
from the other side.

451
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:00,750
Then where should we
get the produce from?

452
00:28:00,791 --> 00:28:01,833
Thatʼs not my problem.

453
00:28:01,833 --> 00:28:02,875
So what can we do now?

454
00:28:02,916 --> 00:28:06,250
Henceforth, you have to take my permission
if you have to do anything in the forest.

455
00:28:07,791 --> 00:28:10,291
Whatʼs the issue?

456
00:28:10,291 --> 00:28:15,333
Shiva, this man says we need his permission
to bring produce from the forest.

457
00:28:16,041 --> 00:28:18,208
Is it?
Do we have to take permission?

458
00:28:18,208 --> 00:28:19,958
The government won't
spare you if you don't.

459
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:23,041
Dammit! We've been living here much before
your government came into the picture.

460
00:28:23,041 --> 00:28:24,875
If you think about it,
you need our permission.

461
00:28:24,916 --> 00:28:27,291
Do you have it?
Speak up.

462
00:28:27,833 --> 00:28:28,833
No, right?

463
00:28:29,583 --> 00:28:31,916
You don’t need any permission Vasanthiakka.
You can go.

464
00:28:32,541 --> 00:28:33,583
Okay!

465
00:28:33,583 --> 00:28:35,291
You guys leave!
It’s so damn hot!

466
00:28:35,333 --> 00:28:37,291
Itʼs a big deal we
let you in the forest!

467
00:28:37,333 --> 00:28:38,375
A map, eh?

468
00:28:38,416 --> 00:28:40,083
Hey, where can I find
Parapaade on the map?

469
00:28:40,333 --> 00:28:41,541
I guess you donʼt know either.

470
00:28:41,583 --> 00:28:43,958
They are also searching for the same!
- Is it? Continue.

471
00:28:45,291 --> 00:28:46,333
Okay, carry on!

472
00:28:47,125 --> 00:28:48,208
Let me know if you find it.

473
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:50,958
Ravi. -
- Sir?

474
00:28:51,416 --> 00:28:53,416
Patrol near Parapaade tonight.
- Okay sir.

475
00:28:54,208 --> 00:28:56,083
Lacchu, have I told you
my grandfather's story?

476
00:28:56,125 --> 00:28:57,458
Damn! There he goes again!

477
00:28:57,458 --> 00:28:58,625
1850.

478
00:28:58,625 --> 00:28:59,916
This was the time of the Kings.

479
00:29:00,166 --> 00:29:02,416
During the reign of
King Gajendra Simha....

480
00:29:02,458 --> 00:29:06,500
The King and my Grandpa Thaniya,
the brave warrior were close friends.

481
00:29:07,291 --> 00:29:10,125
The King once took my
Grandpa for a hunt.

482
00:29:10,250 --> 00:29:12,916
They hunted 14 wild boars in
the course of their banter.

483
00:29:12,958 --> 00:29:14,041
My god!

484
00:29:14,083 --> 00:29:16,083
When they went ahead,
they found another one.

485
00:29:16,083 --> 00:29:18,041
A Wild boar?
- No dude. It was a tiger.

486
00:29:18,083 --> 00:29:19,375
Oh!
What happened?

487
00:29:19,375 --> 00:29:21,208
Shush!
- What is it Shivanna?

488
00:29:27,375 --> 00:29:28,875
Hey! What is it?

489
00:29:29,625 --> 00:29:32,125
I didnʼt spot anything. Did you?

490
00:29:32,291 --> 00:29:34,208
I can't spot
anything but tigers.

491
00:29:39,125 --> 00:29:40,125
[GUNSHOT]

492
00:29:58,833 --> 00:30:00,041
Hey Shiva! What happened?

493
00:30:00,041 --> 00:30:02,416
Nothing dude.
- He shot something, didnʼt he?

494
00:30:02,416 --> 00:30:04,291
Letʼs search for it.
- I didnʼt see it too.

495
00:30:04,333 --> 00:30:05,833
Shiva!
- We wonʼt find it. Letʼs go.

496
00:30:07,125 --> 00:30:08,916
Lacchu,
where were we in the story?

497
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:12,625
The tiger was eyeing
the King as its prey.

498
00:30:12,666 --> 00:30:15,166
But the King was looking
at the tiger as his prey.

499
00:30:15,208 --> 00:30:17,541
He took out the gun and
pressed the trigger.

500
00:30:17,875 --> 00:30:18,875
Boom!

501
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,375
Whatʼs that?
- Boom Boom!

502
00:30:20,416 --> 00:30:22,666
What's happening?!
- The bloody gun didnʼt fire.

503
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,708
The tiger came
pouncing at the king.

504
00:30:24,916 --> 00:30:27,333
Suddenly,
my Grandpa grabbed the Kingʼs gun.

505
00:30:27,375 --> 00:30:31,625
He rammed it against the ground twice, gave it a
jerk, aimed it to the ground and took his shot.

506
00:30:31,791 --> 00:30:32,791
Boom!

507
00:30:32,916 --> 00:30:34,791
The gun fired and the
tiger died on the spot!

508
00:30:34,791 --> 00:30:36,791
How did the tiger die if he
aimed the gun at the ground?

509
00:30:36,833 --> 00:30:39,125
The bullet bounced
off and hit the tiger.

510
00:30:39,166 --> 00:30:40,333
It died on the spot!

511
00:30:40,333 --> 00:30:41,750
What a useless gun!

512
00:30:41,791 --> 00:30:45,583
Shut up! That very gun was gifted to my
Grandpa in the grand court of the the King.

513
00:30:45,583 --> 00:30:46,583
Okay dude.

514
00:30:46,625 --> 00:30:47,625
Shush!

515
00:30:58,625 --> 00:30:59,666
Hey stop!

516
00:30:59,666 --> 00:31:01,125
Itʼs wounded. Letʼs chase it!

517
00:31:01,166 --> 00:31:02,583
I heard a sound from this side.

518
00:31:02,625 --> 00:31:03,875
Rampa, shoot it, idiot!

519
00:31:05,750 --> 00:31:07,625
Heʼs useless!
Why did you bring him?

520
00:31:07,666 --> 00:31:09,458
Iʼm not going to use
this old manʼs gun!

521
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:11,375
If you come hunting again,
Iʼll break your leg!

522
00:31:11,916 --> 00:31:12,916
Fire quickly!

523
00:31:12,958 --> 00:31:14,166
I canʼt fire with this gun!

524
00:31:14,166 --> 00:31:15,833
Go to the other side
and shoot you moron!

525
00:31:15,833 --> 00:31:17,625
Why hold a gun if you
canʼt shoot, bonehead?!

526
00:31:17,625 --> 00:31:20,083
Stand away from me,
else I'll die here.

527
00:31:22,291 --> 00:31:23,291
Come on.

528
00:31:28,791 --> 00:31:30,041
Bloody boar!

529
00:31:30,958 --> 00:31:32,041
Didnʼt I tell you?

530
00:31:32,083 --> 00:31:34,000
My Grandpa's gun never
fails to bring us meat.

531
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:35,125
Look, such a big one!

532
00:31:36,625 --> 00:31:38,541
It’s so huge!
Must be Bullaʼs relative.

533
00:31:39,583 --> 00:31:40,625
Letʼs hunt another one.

534
00:31:40,666 --> 00:31:42,958
Donʼt be an idiot!
We can't do it all over again!

535
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:44,375
One is enough. Letʼs go back.

536
00:31:44,416 --> 00:31:45,875
Is this all youʼre capable of?
Okay then.

537
00:31:45,916 --> 00:31:47,000
Tie it up. Letʼs go.

538
00:31:47,375 --> 00:31:50,375
Didnʼt we shoot a boar here?

539
00:31:50,416 --> 00:31:51,875
We won't find it. Let's go.

540
00:31:52,750 --> 00:31:53,958
Let's try and look here.

541
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:56,125
Look all over and you'll
find your Grandpa's remains.

542
00:31:56,166 --> 00:31:58,333
Was your grandfather buried here too?

543
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:12,333
If your mother finds out about this
hunt, she’ll thrash you.

544
00:32:12,583 --> 00:32:13,791
I won’t let her beat him.

545
00:32:14,416 --> 00:32:15,958
That portion of the meat
is for the Landlord.

546
00:32:15,958 --> 00:32:17,875
The other portion is
for my grandpa’s gun.

547
00:32:17,916 --> 00:32:19,458
Okay, cut the meat now.

548
00:33:00,708 --> 00:33:01,708
Did you have your dinner?

549
00:33:26,125 --> 00:33:28,208
This moron won't get it.

550
00:33:28,250 --> 00:33:29,375
I'll kill you today.

551
00:33:29,708 --> 00:33:30,708
Imbecile!

552
00:33:30,708 --> 00:33:33,166
Did you go hunting again?
You just wonʼt listen!

553
00:33:33,208 --> 00:33:34,416
What's wrong?

554
00:33:34,416 --> 00:33:36,500
What happened?
Let me explain it to you in detail!

555
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:37,541
You mongrel!

556
00:33:37,541 --> 00:33:39,458
Shiva, we're hungry.
Got anything to eat?

557
00:33:39,500 --> 00:33:41,333
No, my mother will
give you a earful! Run!

558
00:33:41,375 --> 00:33:43,083
You guys are here?!
Youʼre the one spoiling him!

559
00:33:43,083 --> 00:33:44,375
Kamala, listen to me.

560
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:45,500
Rampa, come.

561
00:33:45,875 --> 00:33:47,541
Dimwits! Wait for me!

562
00:33:49,166 --> 00:33:51,791
Did it hurt?
- Not really.

563
00:33:51,791 --> 00:33:53,291
Heʼs used to it.

564
00:33:53,291 --> 00:33:54,291
Yes!

565
00:33:55,416 --> 00:33:57,458
Shiva, where were you last night?

566
00:33:57,791 --> 00:33:59,791
My mother was home and
is scared to sleep alone.

567
00:33:59,958 --> 00:34:01,333
I went home to be with her.

568
00:34:01,375 --> 00:34:03,666
Despite you caring for her so
much, she has no sympathy.

569
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:06,541
Stop at Mahadevachariʼs house.
I have some work.

570
00:34:06,833 --> 00:34:08,916
Mahadevanna, How are you?

571
00:34:08,916 --> 00:34:11,125
You guys carry on.
I have to get my bum repaired.

572
00:34:11,166 --> 00:34:12,958
What?
- Sorry, my gun repaired.

573
00:34:19,666 --> 00:34:21,125
Thimmappa, take them in.

574
00:34:21,125 --> 00:34:22,583
Get the others to
unload the vehicle.

575
00:34:25,916 --> 00:34:27,041
Yes, Sudhakar?
- Sir...

576
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:29,666
The thing is...

577
00:34:29,708 --> 00:34:32,125
If payments keep getting delayed,
how do I get the labour folk?

578
00:34:32,125 --> 00:34:33,333
Iʼm helpless too.

579
00:34:33,333 --> 00:34:35,875
Since the RFO is suspended,
none of the bills are getting through.

580
00:34:35,916 --> 00:34:38,375
Sir, you are doing
most of his work.

581
00:34:38,416 --> 00:34:40,375
Wish you could do something
about the payment too.

582
00:34:40,416 --> 00:34:42,416
Give me some time Sudhakar.
I’ll get it done.

583
00:34:42,625 --> 00:34:45,291
Sir, the Landlord had invited you home.
I'd told you.

584
00:34:45,333 --> 00:34:47,458
I forgot.
- I thought so.

585
00:34:47,458 --> 00:34:49,041
Iʼll go.

586
00:34:49,208 --> 00:34:50,375
Okay then. Iʼll take a leave.

587
00:34:51,875 --> 00:34:52,875
All good?

588
00:34:53,750 --> 00:34:58,333
Sir, we heard two gunshots
in the forest yesterday.

589
00:34:58,625 --> 00:35:00,041
Hunting has taken place for sure.

590
00:35:00,041 --> 00:35:01,625
But we didnʼt find them.

591
00:35:01,791 --> 00:35:04,541
However,
we found this near Parapaade.

592
00:35:04,583 --> 00:35:05,583
Whatʼs this?

593
00:35:05,625 --> 00:35:06,958
The head ornament
of the Demigod.

594
00:35:07,750 --> 00:35:09,416
Seems ancient.

595
00:35:12,291 --> 00:35:14,375
It commands more respect
than a King’s crown.

596
00:35:19,166 --> 00:35:20,333
Looks like a massive boar!

597
00:35:21,125 --> 00:35:22,500
Yes. Weighs 40 kilos.

598
00:35:22,541 --> 00:35:24,583
If itʼs leg weighed 40 kilos,
did the boar weigh 500 kilos?

599
00:35:24,625 --> 00:35:26,041
We meant the boar
weighs 40 kilos.

600
00:35:26,083 --> 00:35:29,250
Mohan, there is a bag on
the table inside. Bring it.

601
00:35:29,250 --> 00:35:30,250
Okay Landlord.

602
00:35:30,666 --> 00:35:31,875
One more thing.

603
00:35:32,291 --> 00:35:34,916
Ensure that your land
documents are in place.

604
00:35:34,916 --> 00:35:36,833
The department has
begun the survey.

605
00:35:37,250 --> 00:35:38,333
Really?

606
00:35:38,333 --> 00:35:40,875
Why else did I call you over?
- But they didn't inform me.

607
00:35:40,916 --> 00:35:41,958
Keep quiet.

608
00:35:41,958 --> 00:35:44,375
Keep the correct documents, okay?
- Okay Landlord.

609
00:35:44,416 --> 00:35:46,416
Youʼve been nodding your
heads for many years now.

610
00:35:46,416 --> 00:35:48,083
Our people donʼt
understand these things.

611
00:35:48,125 --> 00:35:50,041
If you donʼt understand,
you must ask me.

612
00:35:50,333 --> 00:35:51,708
Why the hell did
you call me here?

613
00:35:51,708 --> 00:35:53,708
Calm down man! Take it easy.

614
00:35:53,750 --> 00:35:55,375
If we donʼt get it.
You'll handle it, right?

615
00:35:55,375 --> 00:35:56,416
Of course, Iʼm here.

616
00:35:57,541 --> 00:36:00,416
Next time, see if you can
hunt something with spots!

617
00:36:00,458 --> 00:36:01,541
Sure.

618
00:36:01,750 --> 00:36:03,125
Let the Bhootha Kola get over.

619
00:36:03,541 --> 00:36:05,333
What does he mean spotted?
A leopard?

620
00:36:05,375 --> 00:36:06,583
Deer, you idiot!

621
00:36:06,583 --> 00:36:07,583
Give it here.

622
00:36:08,666 --> 00:36:09,958
Take it.

623
00:36:10,083 --> 00:36:11,166
Hey Venkatramana, letʼs go.

624
00:36:15,958 --> 00:36:17,583
Hey Jagga! Mohan!

625
00:36:17,625 --> 00:36:20,291
Load the rice bags, vegetables
and fruits in the officer's jeep.

626
00:36:20,333 --> 00:36:21,708
Take it.
- Pick them up.

627
00:36:23,708 --> 00:36:24,708
Please come!

628
00:36:25,250 --> 00:36:26,333
Whatʼs all this?

629
00:36:26,375 --> 00:36:27,583
Youʼre our guest.

630
00:36:27,625 --> 00:36:29,625
How can I send you
back empty-handed?

631
00:36:29,875 --> 00:36:31,250
Come letʼs chat
over a cup of tea.

632
00:36:34,583 --> 00:36:36,833
Hope things are going
fine in the village.

633
00:36:41,625 --> 00:36:43,625
I hear youʼre set to conduct
survey in our village.

634
00:36:44,791 --> 00:36:46,333
You know our people, right?

635
00:36:46,583 --> 00:36:48,208
Their livelihood
depends on this forest.

636
00:36:48,208 --> 00:36:49,458
They're uneducated.

637
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:51,875
I suggest you grin
and bear with it.

638
00:36:52,375 --> 00:36:55,041
The previous officer was
in good terms with me.

639
00:36:56,041 --> 00:36:58,875
Please ensure that we
donʼt face any troubles.

640
00:36:58,875 --> 00:37:01,333
Iʼd say itʼs better if you
ensure that there is no trouble.

641
00:37:02,166 --> 00:37:03,708
My work will be on.

642
00:37:05,291 --> 00:37:06,875
Let me know when
there are festivals.

643
00:37:06,916 --> 00:37:08,375
Iʼll come over for food.

644
00:37:09,250 --> 00:37:10,583
My wife isnʼt at home.

645
00:37:10,791 --> 00:37:12,916
She left me because I don't
grin and bear with things.

646
00:37:16,625 --> 00:37:17,625
See you.

647
00:37:17,625 --> 00:37:18,625
Sure.

648
00:37:20,125 --> 00:37:22,708
Sir, this is the boundary
of the forest department.

649
00:37:22,708 --> 00:37:24,750
Encroachment has been
noticed in these two regions.

650
00:37:24,750 --> 00:37:27,125
This belongs to Devendra Suttur
and this to the villagers.

651
00:37:27,125 --> 00:37:28,958
I have issued notice to
the concerned parties.

652
00:37:28,958 --> 00:37:31,083
Sending notice to the
villagers wonʼt work.

653
00:37:31,291 --> 00:37:32,541
You have to convince them.

654
00:37:32,541 --> 00:37:34,416
Sir, these villagers
are a little bonkers.

655
00:37:34,416 --> 00:37:36,083
If you confront them,
they pounce on you.

656
00:37:36,083 --> 00:37:37,916
All government officers
say the same story.

657
00:37:38,250 --> 00:37:40,500
But it shouldnʼt become the
excuse for our incompetence.

