Re-telecast of today's news.

1226
01:09:53,666 --> 01:09:58,541
Forest Brigand Veerappan who kidnapped
forest officials in the Satyamangala forest

1227
01:09:58,958 --> 01:10:02,166
has warned to chop off the heads of
the officials if his demands are not.

1228
01:10:02,208 --> 01:10:04,500
Dammit!
Look at how evil the world is.

1229
01:10:04,541 --> 01:10:06,333
Nobody's as innocent as us.
- You're right.

1230
01:10:06,458 --> 01:10:08,416
Brother, give sir a glass of tea.
Itʼs on me.

1231
01:10:09,250 --> 01:10:12,166
Make sure the evil forces are
confined within the borders Guliga.

1232
01:10:12,291 --> 01:10:15,875
♪ A tiger lurks on the edge of the hill ♪

1233
01:10:15,875 --> 01:10:18,083
You said you know this region
well and asked to be posted here.

1234
01:10:18,125 --> 01:10:19,791
Just like the trees,
your reputation too is at stake.

1235
01:10:19,791 --> 01:10:22,958
♪ The wounded King tiger is growling ♪
- Canʼt you see the boar?

1236
01:10:23,000 --> 01:10:26,500
♪ Should it be tied
up or hunted down? ♪

1237
01:10:27,583 --> 01:10:29,250
Looks like hunting is on too!

1238
01:10:29,958 --> 01:10:33,291
♪ It's not a wild tiger
It's a pussy cat ♪

1239
01:10:33,625 --> 01:10:36,833
♪ Look for the thief's
footsteps and find his trail ♪

1240
01:10:37,125 --> 01:10:40,625
♪ Look at the twinkling
eyes in the dark. ♪

1241
01:10:41,458 --> 01:10:43,125
Looks like you caught
a bigger one this time.

1242
01:10:43,166 --> 01:10:44,583
Yes, Landlord.
It's easily 70 kilos.

1243
01:10:46,333 --> 01:10:49,625
You guys are freshers.
I used to hunt as a kid.

1244
01:10:49,666 --> 01:10:51,833
Oh! He doesn't look like a
hunter, does he?

1245
01:10:52,250 --> 01:10:53,958
Take this! You may leave.

1246
01:10:54,333 --> 01:10:56,583
I'll take your leave, Landlord.
- Sure, Thimappa.

1247
01:10:58,875 --> 01:11:00,166
Are you avenging the past?

1248
01:11:00,208 --> 01:11:02,875
You are our forest officer,
why would we seek revenge from you?!

1249
01:11:02,916 --> 01:11:05,083
If ever I find you troubling
the department again,

1250
01:11:05,125 --> 01:11:07,291
...I'll take you for a spin
on the interrogation chair.

1251
01:11:07,333 --> 01:11:08,791
A spin?
Gotta take that ride, eh?

1252
01:11:08,833 --> 01:11:10,125
We'll join you too.

1253
01:11:10,875 --> 01:11:13,375
Your wild animals destroy our crops.
What should we do then?

1254
01:11:13,375 --> 01:11:15,333
Just shoot it.
- We'll at least get meat!

1255
01:11:15,375 --> 01:11:16,666
Shiva, donʼt say such things.

1256
01:11:16,708 --> 01:11:18,916
We have a record of the number
of animals in the forest.

1257
01:11:19,875 --> 01:11:22,208
You better keep a tab on the
number of hunters amongst you.

1258
01:11:22,625 --> 01:11:25,333
If anything goes amiss,
we will get an account of it.

1259
01:11:26,041 --> 01:11:29,708
If thereʼs no permission to hunt,
was the license given to fire on Deepavali?

1260
01:11:29,750 --> 01:11:31,833
Come, letʼs talk.
Why are you running away?

1261
01:11:32,708 --> 01:11:35,083
Raghu Anna, a new check post?
- Yes.

1262
01:11:35,083 --> 01:11:38,083
Recently there's been an increase in thefts.
- Makes sense.

1263
01:11:38,083 --> 01:11:39,875
Good job. See you!

1264
01:11:39,916 --> 01:11:41,041
Okay.

1265
01:11:41,833 --> 01:11:45,000
♪ A snake is sleeping
in its burrow ♪

1266
01:11:45,458 --> 01:11:48,791
♪ Should we scare it with
a stick or feed it milk? ♪

1267
01:11:48,833 --> 01:11:52,166
♪ The wounded King tiger is growling ♪

1268
01:11:52,333 --> 01:11:55,833
♪ Should it be tied
up or hunted down? ♪

1269
01:11:55,875 --> 01:11:59,166
♪ That genius King has nestled
in a pit dug by himself ♪

1270
01:11:59,333 --> 01:12:03,000
♪ Looks like he lies hidden
and is conspiring hard ♪

1271
01:12:04,791 --> 01:12:07,916
♪ The Siruras nature
is all around ♪

1272
01:12:07,916 --> 01:12:11,000
♪ The peacock we saw
has spread its feathers ♪

1273
01:12:15,458 --> 01:12:16,458
Whatʼs that?

1274
01:12:16,875 --> 01:12:20,250
My wife said these leaves
help avoid hair fall.

1275
01:12:20,291 --> 01:12:22,208
Iʼll take this and leave the village.

1276
01:12:22,250 --> 01:12:24,833
You think this forest is
your ancestral property?

1277
01:12:29,791 --> 01:12:32,375
Iʼve been insulted enough times.

1278
01:12:33,375 --> 01:12:34,791
This time...

1279
01:12:35,333 --> 01:12:36,916
I wonʼt tell anyone about it.

1280
01:12:39,375 --> 01:12:42,833
Iʼm not lying. Try this once.

1281
01:12:42,875 --> 01:12:43,916
You'll get your hair back.

1282
01:12:47,875 --> 01:12:49,750
Is this enough?
- I don't want any, sir.

1283
01:12:49,958 --> 01:12:51,500
Have it. Itʼs okay.

1284
01:12:52,416 --> 01:12:53,458
Donʼt hesitate.

1285
01:13:01,375 --> 01:13:03,208
Sir, there wasnʼt enough water.
- Enough?

1286
01:13:03,416 --> 01:13:04,583
There wasnʼt any.

1287
01:13:07,083 --> 01:13:09,500
Sir, I need a favour from you.

1288
01:13:09,625 --> 01:13:10,708
One more peg?

1289
01:13:10,708 --> 01:13:11,875
Thatʼs not what I meant.

1290
01:13:12,458 --> 01:13:15,708
Iʼm fed up of asking the
Landlord for my payment.

1291
01:13:15,833 --> 01:13:19,041
If only the timber tender could
be allotted directly to me…

1292
01:13:19,791 --> 01:13:21,416
You don't have to do
it out of charity.

1293
01:13:22,000 --> 01:13:24,208
I have something for you too.
- What?

1294
01:13:24,333 --> 01:13:26,291
Iʼll help you capture
Shiva and his mates.

1295
01:13:31,916 --> 01:13:35,583
Gurnal, what was Sundar saying
about doing good to the village?

1296
01:13:35,583 --> 01:13:37,375
He wants revenge because
the officer hit him.

1297
01:13:37,416 --> 01:13:38,833
He’s hot tempered.

1298
01:13:39,625 --> 01:13:41,000
What a huge tree!

1299
01:13:41,541 --> 01:13:43,541
Were you caught cutting
down a tree like this?

1300
01:13:43,583 --> 01:13:46,208
It was slightly
smaller than this.

1301
01:13:46,208 --> 01:13:47,583
No wonder you got whacked.

1302
01:13:47,625 --> 01:13:50,041
Donʼt finish it all.
Keep some for me too!

1303
01:13:50,583 --> 01:13:52,416
We will.
You continue cutting the tree.

1304
01:13:52,791 --> 01:13:54,458
What a downpour sir!

1305
01:13:56,083 --> 01:13:57,833
Sir, please go slowly.

1306
01:13:58,333 --> 01:13:59,541
A pothole!

1307
01:14:00,875 --> 01:14:02,041
Sir, shall I drive?

1308
01:14:02,083 --> 01:14:04,125
Murali, letʼs go slowly.

1309
01:14:05,208 --> 01:14:06,250
Mr Murali…

1310
01:14:06,250 --> 01:14:08,083
Donʼt worry. They will be there.

1311
01:14:08,125 --> 01:14:11,000
I hope the information is correct.
- Absolutely sir.

1312
01:14:11,333 --> 01:14:15,333
Those idiots have gained a lot of headweight
from killing eating all the forest animals.

1313
01:14:15,625 --> 01:14:17,875
Let them taste food in jail.
That should teach them!

1314
01:14:18,583 --> 01:14:19,916
Bulla.
- Yes?

1315
01:14:20,375 --> 01:14:23,000
Iʼm sure that rabid dog will lose
his job because of this tree.

1316
01:14:23,000 --> 01:14:26,208
What if he doesnʼt?
- Letʼs do something bigger.

1317
01:14:26,916 --> 01:14:28,250
Tiger skin. Cheetah.

1318
01:14:28,416 --> 01:14:30,166
Do we have elephants here?
- Nope.

1319
01:14:30,625 --> 01:14:32,250
If so,
we could have gone for the tusk.

1320
01:14:36,791 --> 01:14:37,875
[WARNING SIGNALS]

1321
01:14:39,958 --> 01:14:41,125
I think itʼs a nightingale.

1322
01:14:41,125 --> 01:14:43,000
Nightingale my foot! Letʼs go.

1323
01:14:44,416 --> 01:14:45,750
Douse the fire!

1324
01:14:52,916 --> 01:14:54,208
Where are you going Shiva!

1325
01:14:54,250 --> 01:14:55,458
The saw is in the tree.

1326
01:15:07,208 --> 01:15:08,291
Whatʼs that sound?

1327
01:15:08,291 --> 01:15:10,291
I hear something close-by.

1328
01:15:21,125 --> 01:15:22,541
Looks like they
died right there.

1329
01:15:22,583 --> 01:15:25,166
Did you guys cut the
tree to kill him?!

1330
01:15:25,500 --> 01:15:26,666
God! Save us!

1331
01:16:31,359 --> 01:16:33,109
You messed it up big time, Shiva!

1332
01:16:33,150 --> 01:16:34,400
Have you lost it?

1333
01:16:34,400 --> 01:16:36,484
It was not intentional.
- Who will believe you?

1334
01:16:36,525 --> 01:16:39,359
Everyone was aware of your
feud with the first officer!

1335
01:16:39,400 --> 01:16:41,067
This will be considered
as a murder case!

1336
01:16:41,109 --> 01:16:42,109
What can we do now?

1337
01:16:45,692 --> 01:16:47,025
Iʼll handle this.

1338
01:16:47,067 --> 01:16:48,734
You know the forest well, Shiva.

1339
01:16:49,109 --> 01:16:52,067
Abscond for a while.

1340
01:16:58,025 --> 01:16:59,359
I gave them the signal.

1341
01:16:59,400 --> 01:17:01,025
I thought they’d follow me.

1342
01:17:02,609 --> 01:17:03,609
Where is Shiva?

1343
01:17:06,734 --> 01:17:07,859
There's no one here.

1344
01:17:07,900 --> 01:17:09,984
Have they left anything behind?
- Nope.

1345
01:17:10,692 --> 01:17:11,775
Then get down.

1346
01:17:13,692 --> 01:17:16,109
Because of us,
people in the jeep lost their lives.

1347
01:17:16,525 --> 01:17:17,525
Yes.

1348
01:17:17,567 --> 01:17:19,400
We tried to be over smart.

1349
01:17:20,400 --> 01:17:23,192
If we get caught,
weʼll be behind bars.

1350
01:17:23,234 --> 01:17:24,317
You guys leave.

1351
01:17:25,025 --> 01:17:27,109
Iʼll surrender citing
it was my fault.

1352
01:17:28,109 --> 01:17:29,109
Shiva!

1353
01:17:29,859 --> 01:17:31,025
Bas*ard!

1354
01:17:31,442 --> 01:17:34,234
Instead of planning what to do next,
everyone’s worried about the dead!

1355
01:18:49,984 --> 01:18:51,859
If you come close to
me, I'll kill you.

1356
01:18:51,900 --> 01:18:53,567
I'm a fierce warrior!

1357
01:18:54,275 --> 01:18:55,900
Another nightmare?!

1358
01:18:55,900 --> 01:18:57,025
What the heck!

1359
01:18:59,650 --> 01:19:01,400
Don't worry.
Everything will be fine.

1360
01:19:01,692 --> 01:19:03,734
Sacrifice a hen to Guliga
and things will be fine.

1361
01:19:03,775 --> 01:19:06,109
Is Guliga so powerful?
- Of course.

1362
01:19:06,150 --> 01:19:07,817
Guliga is the one who
protects our borders.

1363
01:19:16,609 --> 01:19:17,775
What the hell dude?

1364
01:19:18,067 --> 01:19:19,359
Not a single human in sight!

1365
01:19:19,359 --> 01:19:20,400
Only cops.

1366
01:19:21,442 --> 01:19:23,400
Looks like they are
searching for someone.

1367
01:19:28,359 --> 01:19:30,067
Shiva! Itʼs over there.

1368
01:19:30,109 --> 01:19:31,109
Okay.

1369
01:19:34,317 --> 01:19:36,359
Itʼs not working! Sh*t!

1370
01:19:38,150 --> 01:19:39,359
Landlord, itʼs me Shiva.

1371
01:19:45,192 --> 01:19:47,234
Thankfully,
everyone in the jeep survived.

1372
01:19:47,275 --> 01:19:48,400
We're saved!

1373
01:19:48,442 --> 01:19:50,942
We've to stay low in the forest
until further notice from Landlord.

1374
01:19:50,984 --> 01:19:52,400
Iʼll quickly go
and see my mother.

1375
01:19:52,400 --> 01:19:53,775
The cops are around, Shiva.

1376
01:19:53,817 --> 01:19:54,942
If they come, give a signal.

1377
01:19:54,984 --> 01:19:56,150
To whom? To the Cops or you?

1378
01:19:56,150 --> 01:19:58,234
Signal your dead Grandpa!
- Go home. Get some gun powder, bombs.

1379
01:19:58,234 --> 01:19:59,484
We will need it for hunting.

1380
01:19:59,484 --> 01:20:01,442
Bulla, grab some eatables
from Padmaʼs shop.

1381
01:20:01,525 --> 01:20:03,692
Iʼll see you soon.
- Rampa come along.

1382
01:20:04,234 --> 01:20:05,484
Go inside and get everything.

1383
01:20:07,317 --> 01:20:08,317
Shiva?!

1384
01:20:08,650 --> 01:20:09,650
Shiva!

1385
01:20:09,859 --> 01:20:11,192
I'm done with these people.

1386
01:20:11,525 --> 01:20:13,567
I'll leave town right away.

1387
01:20:26,567 --> 01:20:27,984
No fish curry today?
Thatʼs enough.

1388
01:20:28,234 --> 01:20:30,400
For the sins you’ve
committed, I'm starving here.

1389
01:20:30,442 --> 01:20:31,609
He wants fish curry!

1390
01:20:31,650 --> 01:20:32,942
I can't swallow anything
without fish curry.

1391
01:20:32,942 --> 01:20:34,109
Make it the next time I come.

1392
01:20:34,150 --> 01:20:35,692
Youʼre going back again?

1393
01:20:35,734 --> 01:20:36,859
Iʼll be back soon mother.

1394
01:20:37,109 --> 01:20:38,359
Not like I'm joining the Army.

1395
01:20:41,692 --> 01:20:42,692
Give me a Soda.

1396
01:20:43,525 --> 01:20:44,525
Here.

1397
01:20:46,692 --> 01:20:48,275
Donʼt you have any change dude?

1398
01:20:52,817 --> 01:20:54,567
What an opportunity
at this hour!

1399
01:20:57,275 --> 01:20:58,275
A cop?

1400
01:20:58,984 --> 01:21:00,650
If I run away now,
will you come after me?

1401
01:21:01,192 --> 01:21:02,192
Chanchala!

1402
01:21:02,734 --> 01:21:04,192
Stop right there!

1403
01:21:05,234 --> 01:21:06,734
Sheela, I'm here.

1404
01:21:09,484 --> 01:21:11,484
You guys take your time
and enjoy your food.

1405
01:21:11,525 --> 01:21:13,109
Iʼll wait right outside.

1406
01:21:13,192 --> 01:21:14,567
Please have your dinner and go.

1407
01:21:14,942 --> 01:21:17,234
Don't make me run.
I can't run faster.

1408
01:21:17,734 --> 01:21:18,817
Shiva!

1409
01:21:18,859 --> 01:21:19,859
Look at him eat!

1410
01:21:19,859 --> 01:21:20,984
The cops are here. Run!

1411
01:21:21,317 --> 01:21:23,817
Mother, make fish curry.
I donʼt know when Iʼll come back!

1412
01:21:25,067 --> 01:21:26,359
Cover him from the other side.

1413
01:21:29,525 --> 01:21:31,150
Run guys!

1414
01:21:31,359 --> 01:21:33,609
Iʼll teach those
scoundrels a lesson!

1415
01:21:33,650 --> 01:21:34,734
Hey Abu!

1416
01:21:36,234 --> 01:21:37,359
Why did you throw it?

1417
01:21:37,359 --> 01:21:39,150
If I light and don't throw
it, it'll explode in my hand!

1418
01:21:39,192 --> 01:21:40,650
You're going to get us killed.
Run!

1419
01:21:41,942 --> 01:21:44,067
This is what happens when
you show up at work drunk!

1420
01:21:44,067 --> 01:21:45,192
Are you crazy?

1421
01:21:46,067 --> 01:21:48,359
Sir, we didnʼt
collide with the tree.

1422
01:21:48,484 --> 01:21:50,067
The tree fell on us.

1423
01:21:50,192 --> 01:21:51,900
We didnʼt even
realise what happened.

1424
01:21:51,942 --> 01:21:52,942
Shut up!

1425
01:21:52,942 --> 01:21:55,525
You better stay away from people
like him and focus on work.

1426
01:21:58,359 --> 01:21:59,775
This is all Shivaʼs handiwork.

1427
01:21:59,775 --> 01:22:01,067
This was intentional.

1428
01:22:02,234 --> 01:22:05,109
Ravi, file all the
possible cases on him.

1429
01:22:05,650 --> 01:22:06,984
He should never see daylight.

1430
01:22:31,025 --> 01:22:32,025
Do you hear it too?

1431
01:22:35,484 --> 01:22:36,484
Yes.

1432
01:22:38,775 --> 01:22:40,025
Get up man!

1433
01:22:42,067 --> 01:22:43,067
Hey cops!

1434
01:22:43,067 --> 01:22:44,484
Itʼs a raid! Run!

1435
01:22:44,525 --> 01:22:46,067
Hey Rampanna!

1436
01:22:50,650 --> 01:22:52,650
Leela, the aroma is brilliant!

1437
01:22:53,609 --> 01:22:56,025
Are you dumb?
Why did you bring a stranger here?

1438
01:22:56,025 --> 01:22:59,859
Look at these street mongrels
hogging from a stranger.

1439
01:23:00,067 --> 01:23:01,150
Donʼt eat it idiots!

1440
01:23:05,359 --> 01:23:07,400
You should be lucky
to eat such food.

1441
01:23:07,442 --> 01:23:10,150
Bullsh*t!
My mother cooks better.

1442
01:23:10,192 --> 01:23:11,192
Shiva!

1443
01:23:13,942 --> 01:23:15,275
What a bunch of cowards!

1444
01:23:15,734 --> 01:23:17,900
I ran for my life
and none of you followed me.

1445
01:23:17,900 --> 01:23:19,400
We called you many times.

1446
01:23:19,442 --> 01:23:21,234
But you were too
scared to hear us.

1447
01:23:21,484 --> 01:23:23,609
Leela, have you come alone?

1448
01:23:23,650 --> 01:23:25,984
The next time you come,
please leave your anklets at home.

1449
01:23:26,525 --> 01:23:28,317
Did you all finish eating?

1450
01:23:28,359 --> 01:23:29,359
I didnʼt.

1451
01:23:30,150 --> 01:23:31,775
A man must be stubborn.
- Correct!

1452
01:23:31,775 --> 01:23:32,775
You carry on with it.

1453
01:23:32,817 --> 01:23:34,484
Bulla, hope you’ve left some for me.

1454
01:23:34,525 --> 01:23:35,609
Have it.

1455
01:23:35,609 --> 01:23:37,400
It's okay to be stubborn.
Not arrogant!

1456
01:23:38,400 --> 01:23:39,859
Done serving? Take her away.

1457
01:23:40,234 --> 01:23:41,609
Else Iʼll beat her to death!

1458
01:23:41,609 --> 01:23:43,817
Of course!
Killing people is all you know.

1459
01:23:43,817 --> 01:23:46,567
As if the tree incident, wasnʼt enough,
you’ve thrown bombs on the cops!

1460
01:23:46,609 --> 01:23:48,484
They’re searching for you
in the entire village.

1461
01:23:48,525 --> 01:23:50,442
In no time,
they will arrive here.

1462
01:23:50,692 --> 01:23:51,984
Just go to hell!

1463
01:23:52,234 --> 01:23:53,900
Enough eating!
Give it back!

1464
01:23:54,192 --> 01:23:55,442
Lacchu, come.

1465
01:23:56,192 --> 01:23:58,067
There was a big
piece of fish left.

1466
01:23:58,692 --> 01:24:01,317
She's the one who fenced her
own village on Day 1 of her job.

1467
01:24:01,317 --> 01:24:03,817
I donʼt trust she was
here to just give us food.

1468
01:24:11,525 --> 01:24:12,525
Hey Shiva!

1469
01:24:13,817 --> 01:24:15,567
He went off with my gun!

1470
01:24:25,984 --> 01:24:28,400
You may come inside,
instead of sitting like a guard outside.

1471
01:24:36,859 --> 01:24:38,734
We didn't intentionally
drop the tree on them.

1472
01:24:38,775 --> 01:24:39,859
It was an accident.

1473
01:24:40,442 --> 01:24:42,192
You think I did
things intentionally?

1474
01:24:42,192 --> 01:24:46,317
Though I wasn't at fault in the encroachment
case, you guys treated me like a dog.

1475
01:24:46,359 --> 01:24:48,359
Do you want a job that goes
against your own people?

1476
01:24:48,359 --> 01:24:49,525
Okay, Iʼll quit.

1477
01:24:49,900 --> 01:24:52,692
All my efforts to procure
the job will go in vain.

1478
01:24:53,234 --> 01:24:55,734
If it makes you
happy, Iʼll quit.

1479
01:25:06,275 --> 01:25:07,275
Iʼm sorry.

1480
01:25:07,609 --> 01:25:08,942
No need to put up an act.

1481
01:25:09,567 --> 01:25:10,984
Don't you see I'm apologising?

1482
01:25:11,025 --> 01:25:12,567
To hell with your apology.

1483
01:25:14,442 --> 01:25:16,109
Acting smart when I say sorry?

1484
01:25:16,150 --> 01:25:17,150
No Shiva.

1485
01:25:17,400 --> 01:25:18,400
What?

1486
01:25:18,817 --> 01:25:19,817
No, Shiva.

1487
01:25:22,025 --> 01:25:23,025
What don't you want?

1488
01:25:30,567 --> 01:25:31,650
You stink of beedis.

1489
01:25:32,192 --> 01:25:33,192
Doesn't bother me.

1490
01:25:35,650 --> 01:25:37,650
Remind me to offer
a hen to Guliga.

1491
01:25:37,692 --> 01:25:38,692
Alright.

1492
01:25:45,900 --> 01:25:48,192
Hey Leela!
Why didnʼt you lock the door?

1493
01:25:48,234 --> 01:25:49,775
What if something
dangerous enters home?

1494
01:25:53,234 --> 01:25:54,942
Shivanna?
- Hmm?

1495
01:25:56,317 --> 01:25:57,484
Where were you all this time?

1496
01:25:57,525 --> 01:25:58,525
I was in the forest.

1497
01:25:58,734 --> 01:26:00,942
I felt like seeing you all.
So, I came by.

1498
01:26:01,484 --> 01:26:05,025
Shivanna, in our house,
we use only grated coconut to cook.

1499
01:26:05,025 --> 01:26:06,359
Not the shell.

1500
01:26:10,234 --> 01:26:11,275
Have you eaten?

1501
01:26:12,400 --> 01:26:13,400
Shall we?

1502
01:26:14,442 --> 01:26:15,442
Come.

1503
01:26:16,275 --> 01:26:17,400
Shall we eat?

1504
01:26:18,900 --> 01:26:21,234
Dinner was good.
- I don't know who got the fish.

1505
01:26:21,275 --> 01:26:22,650
Howʼs my husband?

1506
01:26:23,234 --> 01:26:24,234
Heʼs fine.

1507
01:26:24,609 --> 01:26:26,817
You should have brought him too.

1508
01:26:27,692 --> 01:26:29,567
He didnʼt know I was coming.

1509
01:26:32,900 --> 01:26:34,192
Shivanna, leaving already?

1510
01:26:39,859 --> 01:26:42,442
Yes. I will be in
Kailasa for some time.

1511
01:26:42,442 --> 01:26:44,567
Go in. Have your dinner, kids.

1512
01:26:58,567 --> 01:26:59,942
Who told you to come here?

1513
01:27:00,192 --> 01:27:01,817
You could've left
without speaking a word.

1514
01:27:02,234 --> 01:27:04,400
Who were you trying to
inform about Kailasa?

1515
01:27:06,817 --> 01:27:07,817
I was telling you.

1516
01:27:11,900 --> 01:27:13,734
What are you thinking, Shiva?

1517
01:27:14,234 --> 01:27:15,400
I'll surrender.

1518
01:27:16,442 --> 01:27:17,442
Don't Shiva.

1519
01:27:18,192 --> 01:27:23,900
In a situation like this, they'll file random
cases and make sure you never get out of jail.

1520
01:27:28,442 --> 01:27:29,442
That's okay.

1521
01:27:30,275 --> 01:27:31,817
None of you should
suffer because of me.

1522
01:27:32,525 --> 01:27:33,525
Let’s see what happens.

1523
01:27:33,525 --> 01:27:34,609
Shiva!

1524
01:27:40,984 --> 01:27:42,359
It's dawn already. Leave now.

1525
01:27:43,150 --> 01:27:44,150
Go.

1526
01:27:50,984 --> 01:27:51,984
Hello! Good morning!

1527
01:27:54,650 --> 01:27:56,442
Shiva and Leela in Kailasa!

1528
01:27:57,067 --> 01:27:58,442
I had come up a while ago.

1529
01:27:59,359 --> 01:28:02,067
But I didnʼt want to disturb
since you were asleep.

1530
01:28:03,734 --> 01:28:06,817
The enthusiasm you had while climbing,
seems to be missing while getting down!

1531
01:28:10,442 --> 01:28:11,442
Off with you!

1532
01:28:15,109 --> 01:28:18,234
The Government pays your salary,
but you're serving him, eh?

1533
01:28:19,692 --> 01:28:20,692
You leave.

1534
01:28:22,025 --> 01:28:23,400
Donʼt you get it? Go!

1535
01:28:25,817 --> 01:28:27,109
I will handle these morons.

1536
01:28:30,192 --> 01:28:32,234
Why are you butting
in when we're talking?

1537
01:28:32,275 --> 01:28:33,484
Move aside!

1538
01:28:43,400 --> 01:28:46,817
We sure canʼt award
you for your co-operation.

1539
01:28:47,234 --> 01:28:48,317
But I can suspend you.

1540
01:28:49,650 --> 01:28:50,650
Isn’t it Shiva?

1541
01:28:51,734 --> 01:28:52,775
Is it loaded?
- Yes.

1542
01:28:54,109 --> 01:28:56,109
You have to serve
Shiva in his Kailasa.

1543
01:28:57,275 --> 01:29:00,067
You also have to take care of
the Landlord who got you the job.

1544
01:29:01,025 --> 01:29:02,484
Sir!
- Poor girl. Must be tired.

1545
01:29:03,025 --> 01:29:05,317
Rest for some 15 days.
Okay?

1546
01:29:06,609 --> 01:29:08,067
Will you hold a
torch for this too?

1547
01:29:08,817 --> 01:29:10,900
Itʼs Shivaʼs gun.
It's loaded sir!

1548
01:29:11,984 --> 01:29:12,984
Come forward!

1549
01:29:15,192 --> 01:29:16,192
Come.

1550
01:29:23,817 --> 01:29:24,859
Sir!

1551
01:29:26,484 --> 01:29:27,984
Move aside.

1552
01:29:31,234 --> 01:29:32,817
Where are you taking him?

1553
01:29:34,734 --> 01:29:35,734
I said move aside.

1554
01:29:40,442 --> 01:29:45,567
[INDISTINCT COMMOTION]

1555
01:30:06,067 --> 01:30:07,734
Shiva,
what happened to your face?

1556
01:30:07,775 --> 01:30:09,150
Forget that.
How did they catch you?

1557
01:30:09,192 --> 01:30:12,150
This bonehead went for a girl
but returned with the cops.

1558
01:30:12,150 --> 01:30:13,192
Moron!

1559
01:30:13,650 --> 01:30:15,442
Sorry.
- Pervert!

1560
01:30:15,775 --> 01:30:16,900
Obsessed with women.

1561
01:30:17,109 --> 01:30:19,275
Irresponsible brutes!
- Where were you?

1562
01:30:20,150 --> 01:30:21,234
Thought so.

1563
01:30:21,275 --> 01:30:23,859
As if you're
extremely responsible!

1564
01:30:26,692 --> 01:30:28,484
I had told him not
to leave his hideout.

1565
01:30:28,859 --> 01:30:29,984
His bad luck.

1566
01:30:32,067 --> 01:30:33,192
Good thing.

1567
01:30:33,984 --> 01:30:35,192
He was flying high.

1568
01:30:35,400 --> 01:30:37,400
Please donʼt bail him out.

1569
01:30:38,442 --> 01:30:41,567
If I don't do what's on my mind,
I won't be at peace, Sudhakar.

1570
01:31:01,775 --> 01:31:03,650
Landlord, itʼs me Guruva.
- Tell me.

1571
01:31:05,317 --> 01:31:06,942
Our land issues have
reached the prison.

1572
01:31:07,942 --> 01:31:09,692
Looks like a disaster awaits us.

1573
01:31:10,650 --> 01:31:12,109
You must set things
right Landlord.

1574
01:31:12,317 --> 01:31:13,984
Did you call at this
hour to tell me this?

1575
01:31:15,609 --> 01:31:18,359
Donʼt worry Guruva.
Iʼll take care of it.

1576
01:31:20,692 --> 01:31:21,984
What did he say?

1577
01:31:22,609 --> 01:31:24,275
He wants me to set things right.

1578
01:31:25,525 --> 01:31:28,692
No matter what happens,
everything must go right, Sudha.

1579
01:31:29,109 --> 01:31:33,234
In connection with the attack on forest
officers in the Kaadubettu region,

1580
01:31:33,275 --> 01:31:37,109
after carefully considering
the evidence presented till date

1581
01:31:37,150 --> 01:31:48,942
Taking IPC section 307, 353, 447, 394 and the
Forest Conservation Act 33 into account...

1582
01:31:48,984 --> 01:31:51,859
The permission to transfer
Shiva and his associates

1583
01:31:51,900 --> 01:31:54,900
to the prison as suspects
during the trial has been granted.

1584
01:31:55,192 --> 01:31:56,192
Take them inside.

1585
01:31:56,567 --> 01:31:58,859
Aren't there any women here?
- That's a different section.

1586
01:31:59,192 --> 01:32:00,192
Hope everything's fine.

1587
01:32:07,192 --> 01:32:09,359
Looks like she is still
angry with my family.

1588
01:32:09,359 --> 01:32:10,609
Nothing of that sort.

1589
01:32:10,859 --> 01:32:14,025
Please bail Shiva
and the others out.

1590
01:32:14,025 --> 01:32:16,192
Itʼs an attempt to murder
case on government official.

1591
01:32:16,984 --> 01:32:18,275
He wonʼt get bail for it.

1592
01:32:19,150 --> 01:32:20,400
Getting him out won't be easy.

1593
01:32:26,984 --> 01:32:31,525
♪ When a man stumbles
upon the stone of fate ♪

1594
01:32:31,817 --> 01:32:36,150
♪ Would the injury on
a finger disappear? ♪

1595
01:32:36,192 --> 01:32:41,400
♪ For fools who get involved under
the influence of hate and anger. ♪

1596
01:32:41,442 --> 01:32:46,525
♪ God doesn't wait
in the temple ♪

1597
01:32:47,400 --> 01:32:51,484
♪ Did the lamp meant to
light up the darkness ♪

1598
01:32:51,484 --> 01:32:56,442
♪ End up turning into a flame
that burnt the entire town down? ♪

1599
01:33:01,942 --> 01:33:03,817
You got food for me? What is it?

1600
01:33:04,817 --> 01:33:05,817
Itʼs fish curry.

1601
01:33:13,567 --> 01:33:14,567
Wow!

1602
01:33:15,192 --> 01:33:16,359
Why are you crying girl?

1603
01:33:16,859 --> 01:33:18,400
Iʼll get you ice-candy
when I come out.

1604
01:33:21,609 --> 01:33:22,942
Didnʼt you bring a match box?

1605
01:33:28,400 --> 01:33:29,400
Thanks!

1606
01:33:32,275 --> 01:33:33,817
Bye.
Take care.

1607
01:33:35,025 --> 01:33:36,775
Shivanna,
Iʼm learning to ride the bike.

1608
01:33:36,817 --> 01:33:38,484
Is it? Good to know.

1609
01:33:46,109 --> 01:33:47,109
Give it to Guruva.

1610
01:33:50,650 --> 01:33:52,650
Guruva, I've prayed for Shiva.

1611
01:33:52,692 --> 01:33:54,109
Donʼt worry about it.

1612
01:33:54,234 --> 01:33:55,484
Iʼm arranging for his bail.

1613
01:33:55,775 --> 01:33:57,192
Inform Kamala.
- Okay.

1614
01:34:04,442 --> 01:34:06,234
Guruva,
where are you coming from?

1615
01:34:06,234 --> 01:34:08,692
Itʼs Sankranthi (festival), right?
I'd gone to Bhandara mansion.

1616
01:34:08,692 --> 01:34:10,817
Good that I met you. Come sit.

1617
01:34:10,859 --> 01:34:12,359
Landlord,
how can I come with you?

1618
01:34:12,692 --> 01:34:14,817
Thatʼs only when others are around.
Hop in.

1619
01:34:17,650 --> 01:34:19,150
Did you have anything to talk about?

1620
01:34:19,484 --> 01:34:20,609
There are many things.

1621
01:34:20,650 --> 01:34:21,859
Letʼs speak as we go.

1622
01:34:24,984 --> 01:34:28,525
Mahadeva! Does this count
as your own courtyard?

1623
01:34:28,775 --> 01:34:30,400
Move aside man!

1624
01:34:33,234 --> 01:34:34,734
Annoying fellow!

1625
01:34:35,650 --> 01:34:36,984
What else Guruva?

1626
01:34:37,775 --> 01:34:39,275
How is your life going?

1627
01:34:39,317 --> 01:34:40,650
It was peaceful until now.

1628
01:34:40,692 --> 01:34:42,317
Youʼre well aware
of how it is now.

1629
01:34:42,734 --> 01:34:44,150
All will be well. Donʼt worry.

1630
01:34:44,400 --> 01:34:45,859
Iʼm asking only about your life.

1631
01:34:46,525 --> 01:34:50,025
With your meagre
earnings, are you happy?

1632
01:34:50,234 --> 01:34:51,775
Itʼs enough to get by.

1633
01:34:52,692 --> 01:34:54,817
Life is not for just getting by.

1634
01:34:54,859 --> 01:34:55,859
One must experience it.

1635
01:35:01,400 --> 01:35:02,984
Let me show you something.

1636
01:35:05,317 --> 01:35:06,567
Guruva, come along.

1637
01:35:07,650 --> 01:35:10,567
Our family owns a lot of land.

1638
01:35:10,984 --> 01:35:17,067
It starts from here in Kaadubettu
and spans until that hillock.

1639
01:35:17,109 --> 01:35:18,359
It spans over 500 acres.

1640
01:35:19,109 --> 01:35:20,942
I own all of this. How is it?

1641
01:35:22,400 --> 01:35:23,484
It's a nice place.

1642
01:35:24,734 --> 01:35:27,442
Guruva, youʼre serving
our Demigod sincerely.

1643
01:35:28,359 --> 01:35:30,109
This is my token of
gratitude for that work.

1644
01:35:31,109 --> 01:35:33,359
Iʼm giving you five
acres of this land.

1645
01:35:33,400 --> 01:35:34,400
God bless.

1646
01:35:37,150 --> 01:35:38,775
Do you seek anything
from me Landlord?

1647
01:35:38,817 --> 01:35:40,317
What will you do for me?
Come on now.

1648
01:35:40,484 --> 01:35:42,109
I'll drop you to Kaadubettu.

1649
01:35:44,025 --> 01:35:45,984
It's okay. I'll manage.

1650
01:35:47,025 --> 01:35:48,067
No oneʼs around.

1651
01:35:49,484 --> 01:35:50,525
Okay.

1652
01:35:50,567 --> 01:35:51,900
This is where we are.

1653
01:35:52,234 --> 01:35:55,525
If we take a right and go straight
from there, is the bathing area.

1654
01:35:55,525 --> 01:35:56,942
Now is not the time to bathe.

1655
01:35:56,942 --> 01:35:58,359
Damn! Be quiet.
You go on.

1656
01:35:58,775 --> 01:36:02,734
Take a left from there and
youʼll find the toilet.

1657
01:36:02,734 --> 01:36:04,484
God knows how long
he'll take to be done.

1658
01:36:04,525 --> 01:36:05,984
Shut up! Go on.

1659
01:36:05,984 --> 01:36:07,567
Thereʼs an alley next to it.

1660
01:36:07,984 --> 01:36:12,025
If we go straight,
thereʼs a 15-foot wall.

1661
01:36:12,859 --> 01:36:15,650
Each of us is at
least five foot tall.

1662
01:36:15,692 --> 01:36:16,817
I'm 5.5ft tall.

1663
01:36:16,817 --> 01:36:20,275
If we get up on each other, we'll be
able to jump over to the other side.

1664
01:36:20,317 --> 01:36:21,775
Freedom! Howʼs the idea?

1665
01:36:23,359 --> 01:36:24,359
Well done.

1666
01:36:24,775 --> 01:36:26,442
Who will be the last man standing?
You?

1667
01:36:26,484 --> 01:36:27,817
Why not? Iʼm six feet tall.

1668
01:36:27,817 --> 01:36:28,817
How will you jump?

1669
01:36:32,234 --> 01:36:36,442
Canʼt you come back and open
the gate after youʼve jumped?

1670
01:36:36,484 --> 01:36:38,859
Like you're father's waiting
to get you out! Dimwit!

1671
01:36:39,150 --> 01:36:41,109
I donʼt think you
understood what I said.

1672
01:36:41,150 --> 01:36:42,525
Let me explain again.
- Damn you!

1673
01:36:42,525 --> 01:36:43,734
This is where we are.

1674
01:36:43,775 --> 01:36:45,150
Let's skip this
Prison break idea.

1675
01:36:45,192 --> 01:36:47,192
Let's take the legal route.
We'll be fine.

1676
01:36:47,234 --> 01:36:49,567
All of you, go and have lunch!

1677
01:36:50,109 --> 01:36:52,317
This is what I love about prison.
Food's always on time.

1678
01:36:54,150 --> 01:36:55,150
What is this?

1679
01:36:59,650 --> 01:37:00,817
We were just drawing.

1680
01:37:00,859 --> 01:37:02,150
Who do you think
you're bluffing with?

1681
01:37:02,192 --> 01:37:03,234
No food for you today.

1682
01:37:03,734 --> 01:37:05,650
Man, you're really cursed.

1683
01:37:05,692 --> 01:37:06,942
You get beaten up all the time!

1684
01:37:26,525 --> 01:37:27,609
Hey Lacchu!

1685
01:37:27,650 --> 01:37:29,734
Looks like they brought back Shiva.

1686
01:37:39,359 --> 01:37:40,984
Where are we going?
What happened?

1687
01:37:41,025 --> 01:37:42,359
I donʼt know. A jeep passed by.

1688
01:37:42,525 --> 01:37:44,109
Thimappa, give me the matchbox.

1689
01:37:57,734 --> 01:37:58,775
Itʼs Guruva!

1690
01:37:59,484 --> 01:38:03,234
Guruva! What happened to you?

1691
01:38:03,900 --> 01:38:06,609
Guruva!

1692
01:38:12,692 --> 01:38:16,109
[CROWD WAILS]

1693
01:38:22,775 --> 01:38:24,234
Guruva!
- Brother, we lost him!

1694
01:38:29,025 --> 01:38:30,442
Oh god!

1695
01:38:33,067 --> 01:38:34,484
Guruva!

1696
01:39:29,900 --> 01:39:32,359
Give us poison and
kill us at once!

1697
01:39:32,734 --> 01:39:34,025
He's mum now.

1698
01:40:08,192 --> 01:40:10,400
We now have no one left!

1699
01:40:18,525 --> 01:40:20,150
The Landlord is entering the house.

1700
01:40:20,192 --> 01:40:21,192
Yeah.

1701
01:40:21,817 --> 01:40:22,817
Greetings Landlord!

1702
01:40:39,692 --> 01:40:41,150
A good-hearted soul.

1703
01:40:41,442 --> 01:40:42,734
He had no enemies.

1704
01:40:44,025 --> 01:40:45,150
Who dared to do this?

1705
01:40:45,150 --> 01:40:48,859
Whoever it is,
the Demigod will not spare him.

1706
01:40:49,442 --> 01:40:51,734
He will die vomiting blood.

1707
01:40:52,525 --> 01:40:54,067
Did you lodge a
complaint with the cops?

1708
01:40:54,109 --> 01:40:56,484
I asked to.
But theyʼre not willing to.

1709
01:40:57,359 --> 01:40:59,109
Why?
- He had the soul of the demi god.

1710
01:40:59,150 --> 01:41:02,067
Does it seem right to slash that body
under the pretext of a post-mortem?

1711
01:41:02,067 --> 01:41:03,400
It wonʼt just be that.

1712
01:41:03,900 --> 01:41:06,400
They will separate the soul
and the body and give it to us.

1713
01:41:06,442 --> 01:41:08,317
That body has experienced
enough pain already.

1714
01:41:08,775 --> 01:41:10,567
Letʼs not lodge a complaint.

1715
01:41:11,359 --> 01:41:13,150
At least,
let his soul rest in peace.

1716
01:41:13,442 --> 01:41:15,067
Letʼs inform Shiva.

1717
01:41:15,109 --> 01:41:17,942
If we tell him,
the cops will accompany him here.

1718
01:41:17,984 --> 01:41:20,484
Let the funeral rites get over.
We can inform him after that.

1719
01:41:20,525 --> 01:41:22,734
They mark the land thatʼs
been with us for ages.

1720
01:41:23,025 --> 01:41:24,609
Our kids go to jail.

1721
01:41:25,025 --> 01:41:27,067
A man who served the
Demigod drops dead.

1722
01:41:27,400 --> 01:41:28,567
What is happening here?!

1723
01:41:28,567 --> 01:41:30,025
Is this land cursed?

1724
01:41:30,150 --> 01:41:31,775
The curse can be removed.

1725
01:41:32,817 --> 01:41:37,150
By the time the mourning period is over,
I will destroy whoever killed Guruva.

1726
01:41:37,692 --> 01:41:39,025
All the village attendees!

1727
01:41:39,025 --> 01:41:42,234
The one who was serving the Demigod
has left to the feet of Lord Guru.

1728
01:41:42,234 --> 01:41:45,150
Until the another person is
appointed as the next monarch....

1729
01:41:45,150 --> 01:41:48,150
I shall now take out the
Guruva's symbolic attire.

1730
01:41:51,859 --> 01:41:56,609
♪ O'! An injured womb is a painful fate ♪

1731
01:41:56,900 --> 01:42:01,734
♪ Yet you wander all your
life to find a cure ♪

1732
01:42:02,484 --> 01:42:06,275
♪ In a conflict with
an invisible opponent ♪

1733
01:42:06,525 --> 01:42:11,484
♪ You shall lose yourself amidst
the task of finding oneself ♪

1734
01:42:12,067 --> 01:42:21,359
♪ Despite dissolving our sings, Goddess Gange
will leave you and me with repentance ♪

1735
01:42:24,067 --> 01:42:33,317
♪ What will you do when the fresh garland of
flower received in pride, withers away tomorrow? ♪

1736
01:42:45,317 --> 01:42:47,025
Kamala!
All of you are here to see me.

1737
01:42:47,609 --> 01:42:48,609
How are you?

1738
01:42:48,609 --> 01:42:49,609
Iʼm fine!

1739
01:42:49,942 --> 01:42:51,192
How are you all doing?

1740
01:42:52,650 --> 01:42:54,150
Did you go hunting?

1741
01:42:55,234 --> 01:42:56,234
How are you dear?

1742
01:42:57,025 --> 01:42:59,400
Kamala, buy her an ice-candy.

1743
01:42:59,400 --> 01:43:00,859
Sheʼs sobbing all the time!

1744
01:43:00,984 --> 01:43:03,150
I don't want you to
perform Bhoota Kola.

1745
01:43:03,150 --> 01:43:04,150
What?

1746
01:43:06,442 --> 01:43:08,609
What the hell man!
Why are you talking so strangely?

1747
01:43:12,650 --> 01:43:13,817
Whatʼs the matter?

1748
01:43:14,650 --> 01:43:15,984
Why should I perform
Bhootha Kola?

1749
01:43:16,234 --> 01:43:17,400
Guruva is doing it anyway.

1750
01:43:20,900 --> 01:43:21,900
He's doing it, right?

1751
01:43:22,275 --> 01:43:24,525
You will not perform the Kola.
Ever.

1752
01:43:36,692 --> 01:43:39,525
What happened?
- Guruva was stabbed to death.

1753
01:43:41,317 --> 01:43:44,900
They threw his corpse in a
jeep near the Kola arena.

1754
01:43:50,817 --> 01:43:51,817
Shiva!

1755
01:43:51,942 --> 01:43:52,942
Hey Shiva!

1756
01:44:21,942 --> 01:44:26,109
Murali, just 'cause the documents were
submitted, the encroachment issue won't end.

1757
01:44:26,150 --> 01:44:29,150
If the villagers donʼt support
you, the fight will continue.

1758
01:44:29,900 --> 01:44:32,109
It's not easy to convert a
forest into a reserve forest.

1759
01:44:32,317 --> 01:44:33,817
Drop your ego and work.

1760
01:44:36,984 --> 01:44:40,275
Sir, people of Kaadubettu
have replied through court.

1761
01:44:40,275 --> 01:44:42,275
Looks like your villagers
finally found the time.

1762
01:44:42,567 --> 01:44:45,484
People feel the heat only
when their as* is on fire.

1763
01:44:50,484 --> 01:44:52,025
Raghu, get the jeep.
- Why sir?

1764
01:44:52,442 --> 01:44:54,900
The scoundrel Landlord has
replied to the encroachment issue.

1765
01:44:54,900 --> 01:44:56,567
Devendra Suttur?
How is that possible?

1766
01:44:56,734 --> 01:44:58,692
Arenʼt the land owners
supposed to reply?

1767
01:44:58,859 --> 01:45:01,067
Letʼs find out.
- It's all over.

1768
01:45:01,109 --> 01:45:03,484
All the land has been transferred
to the Landlord's name.

1769
01:45:04,150 --> 01:45:06,067
All the documents
are now in his name.

1770
01:45:06,775 --> 01:45:08,025
Take care of the file.

1771
01:45:09,359 --> 01:45:13,400
Every time there has been survey,
that shmuck has claimed twenty acres more!

1772
01:45:13,400 --> 01:45:16,734
Thatʼs how his ancestors
have always been.

1773
01:45:16,859 --> 01:45:19,275
But we are not like that.

1774
01:45:19,275 --> 01:45:20,609
We have retained
the same measure.

1775
01:45:23,109 --> 01:45:24,442
Get the area map.

1776
01:45:24,900 --> 01:45:25,900
Whatʼs this?

1777
01:45:25,900 --> 01:45:27,900
I have to tell you something.
- What?

1778
01:45:27,942 --> 01:45:31,859
At one point of time, a fight broke out
putting an end to the Kola procession.

1779
01:45:32,067 --> 01:45:35,525
My family took over the rituals
again and we were taking care of it.

1780
01:45:35,567 --> 01:45:37,984
What if he gets out on bail?
- He won't.

1781
01:45:38,567 --> 01:45:40,109
No way.
- Really?

1782
01:45:40,317 --> 01:45:43,817
Only if he gets a great
lawyer, he might.

1783
01:45:43,942 --> 01:45:46,359
[ON CALL] Does that scammer
Devendra own so much land?

1784
01:45:48,484 --> 01:45:50,359
Ay! Thatʼs the area map.

1785
01:45:50,650 --> 01:45:51,984
A map?

1786
01:45:53,192 --> 01:45:54,734
Of what use is it now?

1787
01:45:54,734 --> 01:45:56,609
People have already
written off their land!

1788
01:45:56,984 --> 01:46:00,734
All documents required to convert
Kaadubettu into a reserve forest are ready.

1789
01:46:01,442 --> 01:46:05,484
If this file moves, the Landlord's
documents will become null and void.

1790
01:46:05,942 --> 01:46:09,400
Your Landlord will have to bow
down before the Lord in the Courts.

1791
01:46:09,442 --> 01:46:10,859
Do as you wish.

1792
01:46:10,900 --> 01:46:13,984
This Bhandara mansion's
Rajeeva is always with you.

1793
01:46:15,192 --> 01:46:16,775
Shiva should have
been with us now.

1794
01:46:24,359 --> 01:46:26,359
Bail out Shiva soon.

1795
01:46:26,442 --> 01:46:29,484
Wow! Change of mind so soon?

1796
01:46:29,525 --> 01:46:31,900
Didnʼt you say a while
ago not to bail him out?

1797
01:46:31,942 --> 01:46:34,025
Iʼm the one telling you
now to bail him out.

1798
01:46:35,275 --> 01:46:39,150
Is it some chicken coop to
open and release it so quickly?

1799
01:46:39,525 --> 01:46:40,775
Itʼs a prison!

1800
01:46:41,275 --> 01:46:42,775
Are you high?

1801
01:46:43,234 --> 01:46:44,942
Can you do it or not?

1802
01:46:44,942 --> 01:46:45,942
I can.

1803
01:46:46,442 --> 01:46:48,109
But itʼs a little tough.

1804
01:46:48,859 --> 01:46:50,817
If we spend some money, we can.

1805
01:46:50,859 --> 01:46:53,775
Iʼll speak to Subba Rao.

1806
01:47:17,234 --> 01:47:18,234
Hello?

1807
01:47:23,317 --> 01:47:26,484
Once upon a time,
there lived a king.

1808
01:47:26,942 --> 01:47:27,942
Just like you.

1809
01:47:30,025 --> 01:47:37,984
From then on, for generations,
everyone kept worshipping the stone.

1810
01:47:38,775 --> 01:47:43,775
From then on, for generations,
everyone kept worshipping the stone.

1811
01:47:44,067 --> 01:47:48,067
When one generation
decided to reclaim the land...

1812
01:47:50,442 --> 01:47:52,942
Instead of shutting their traps
and taking the land back...

1813
01:47:53,525 --> 01:47:55,359
They decided to ask
the Demigod about it.

1814
01:47:55,734 --> 01:47:57,109
The Demigod...

1815
01:47:57,525 --> 01:47:58,942
Wait. No!

1816
01:48:00,525 --> 01:48:02,734
The one wearing the
Demigod's costume...

1817
01:48:04,234 --> 01:48:08,567
The performer told the Landlord that if he messed
with the land, he would die vomiting blood.

1818
01:48:08,984 --> 01:48:12,984
The Landlord realized that
it was the performer talking.

1819
01:48:13,359 --> 01:48:16,650
Is this the Demigod speaking?
Or is it the performer?

1820
01:48:16,650 --> 01:48:20,234
The performer who was caught
red-handed ran away in shame.

1821
01:48:22,317 --> 01:48:23,650
What happened after that?

1822
01:48:24,900 --> 01:48:27,984
Then the Landlord
died of old age.

1823
01:48:28,317 --> 01:48:32,692
The Landlordʼs son in the hope that
at least he could reclaim the land...

1824
01:48:32,734 --> 01:48:34,234
Come on! Let me drop you.

1825
01:48:35,609 --> 01:48:36,734
How can I help you Landlord?

1826
01:48:36,775 --> 01:48:37,775
Guruva.

1827
01:48:38,192 --> 01:48:39,817
I will give you some of my land.

1828
01:48:40,567 --> 01:48:43,150
In return, you must ensure I get
back the land I own in your village.

1829
01:48:43,150 --> 01:48:44,650
How is it possible, Landlord?

1830
01:48:44,650 --> 01:48:48,150
Eons ago, when the Demigod claimed the
land, it was given to the villagers.

1831
01:48:48,650 --> 01:48:52,942
From now on, Guruva must speak at the
Bhootha Kola instead of the Demigod.

1832
01:48:52,942 --> 01:48:54,692
Why are you talking like
this, Landlord?

1833
01:48:54,692 --> 01:48:57,109
Once we don the finery,
it it is the Demigod that takes over.

1834
01:48:57,109 --> 01:48:58,275
Nothing is in my hand

1835
01:48:58,650 --> 01:49:01,234
The Demigod appears
only once a while.

1836
01:49:01,650 --> 01:49:03,900
The rest of the time,
isnʼt it Guruva who speaks?

1837
01:49:07,775 --> 01:49:11,192
To satisfy your greed,
I can't speak as you desire.

1838
01:49:12,317 --> 01:49:13,817
The Demigod will
not appreciate this.

1839
01:49:15,317 --> 01:49:18,317
Itʼs not wrong to reclaim our
land, right?

1840
01:49:22,067 --> 01:49:23,067
Landlord!

1841
01:49:27,775 --> 01:49:30,317
What have you achieved by gaining
the Demigod's appreciation?

1842
01:49:35,900 --> 01:49:37,942
I canʼt believe
youʼre saying this.

1843
01:49:40,234 --> 01:49:41,984
The villagers have a
lot of respect for you.

1844
01:49:44,609 --> 01:49:45,650
If they get to know...

1845
01:49:50,275 --> 01:49:51,442
How will they know?

1846
01:49:52,067 --> 01:49:53,067
Will you tell them?

1847
01:49:53,650 --> 01:49:54,859
Will you?

1848
01:49:55,984 --> 01:49:56,984
Oh!

1849
01:49:58,192 --> 01:49:59,192
The Demigod will?

1850
01:50:01,192 --> 01:50:02,275
The Demigod might, right?

1851
01:50:02,317 --> 01:50:08,525
For the sake of that land, he dealt with the man
who was cheating us in the name of a stone.

1852
01:50:16,025 --> 01:50:18,359
Do you even know the
value of 100 acres?

1853
01:50:18,359 --> 01:50:21,317
You got it for free.
How will you know itʼs value?

1854
01:50:26,275 --> 01:50:28,609
I asked you to set things
right, Landlord.

1855
01:50:31,400 --> 01:50:33,234
I donʼt think you
realise what you've done.

1856
01:50:33,359 --> 01:50:36,109
If I need to set things right,
what is the use of your Demigod?

1857
01:50:37,817 --> 01:50:39,775
From now on,
Iʼll speak on behalf of the Demigod.

1858
01:50:46,900 --> 01:50:49,192
Then?
- It was a blunder.

1859
01:50:49,609 --> 01:50:51,567
Letʼs dispose his
body over there.

1860
01:50:53,525 --> 01:50:55,859
When there is plenty of
space in the forest...

1861
01:50:56,817 --> 01:50:58,359
Why are you keen on
disposing it there?

1862
01:50:58,359 --> 01:50:59,567
I have to.

1863
01:51:00,025 --> 01:51:03,025
For those fools who are
freeloading on my land for years...

1864
01:51:03,442 --> 01:51:05,359
This will serve as a warning.

1865
01:51:16,067 --> 01:51:17,650
After that?

1866
01:51:17,775 --> 01:51:19,775
Let's find out what lies next.

1867
01:51:19,900 --> 01:51:20,900
Okay?

1868
01:51:33,900 --> 01:51:36,484
People will respect us more when
we walk out of the prison, right?

1869
01:51:36,525 --> 01:51:38,692
We went in because
of your stupid gun!

1870
01:51:40,942 --> 01:51:42,525
Didnʼt you bring the axe, boy?
- No.

1871
01:51:42,984 --> 01:51:43,984
You should have.

1872
01:51:46,109 --> 01:51:47,442
Youʼve lost so much hair.

1873
01:51:47,859 --> 01:51:49,275
There is a plant in the forest…

1874
01:51:49,275 --> 01:51:53,109
A plant? Shove it up your…!

1875
01:51:53,525 --> 01:51:54,859
Any updates on Guruvaʼs death?

1876
01:51:56,525 --> 01:51:57,984
He got you out on bail.

1877
01:51:59,984 --> 01:52:01,192
Thank you.

1878
01:52:01,234 --> 01:52:02,484
I have to speak to you, Shiva.

1879
01:52:02,900 --> 01:52:05,900
Shiva, the Landlord
has called you home.

1880
01:52:05,942 --> 01:52:07,984
You donʼt have to go anywhere.
Come home.

1881
01:52:08,442 --> 01:52:09,442
Give me the key.

1882
01:52:09,734 --> 01:52:10,775
You guys come in the jeep.

1883
01:52:10,942 --> 01:52:13,275
Back to your old ways, you dog!

1884
01:52:13,275 --> 01:52:14,650
It was a mistake to get you bail!

1885
01:52:14,650 --> 01:52:17,692
Where are you off
to now scoundrel?

1886
01:52:20,817 --> 01:52:22,150
Shiva!

1887
01:52:24,400 --> 01:52:25,442
Shiva?

1888
01:52:30,442 --> 01:52:34,150
Shiva! Itʼs been so
long since I saw you!

1889
01:52:34,484 --> 01:52:37,525
Come. Hope things were fine in the prison.
- Yes.

1890
01:52:38,442 --> 01:52:40,025
I heard Rajeev bailed you out.

1891
01:52:40,067 --> 01:52:41,525
To get close to you I guess!

1892
01:52:42,567 --> 01:52:43,859
His family is known for it.

1893
01:52:43,900 --> 01:52:48,109
When the Bhootha Kola stopped, he took
the Demigod's ornaments to his house!

1894
01:52:48,150 --> 01:52:49,359
I have to speak to you.

1895
01:52:49,359 --> 01:52:51,192
So do I!

1896
01:52:51,234 --> 01:52:53,567
But first, let us party!

1897
01:52:55,317 --> 01:52:58,234
The Landlord always has scotch.
- What about Guddi?

1898
01:52:58,525 --> 01:52:59,817
Guddi drinks Landlord's scotch.

1899
01:52:59,817 --> 01:53:01,650
Heʼs drinking away to glory!

1900
01:53:02,442 --> 01:53:04,567
He doesnʼt get high easily.

1901
01:53:05,317 --> 01:53:06,609
Thatʼs why I gave him scotch.

1902
01:53:07,484 --> 01:53:09,359
He says youʼre high.

1903
01:53:09,859 --> 01:53:11,025
No Landlord.

1904
01:53:11,817 --> 01:53:13,734
I drink in buckets.

1905
01:53:14,359 --> 01:53:15,484
This is nothing.

1906
01:53:24,192 --> 01:53:25,734
I have something to ask you.

1907
01:53:25,775 --> 01:53:26,775
Go on.

1908
01:53:29,275 --> 01:53:33,109
Who killed our Guruva?

1909
01:53:34,609 --> 01:53:35,609
Why?

1910
01:53:37,150 --> 01:53:38,150
You!

1911
01:53:39,400 --> 01:53:40,400
You!

1912
01:53:41,525 --> 01:53:42,734
You should be with us.

1913
01:53:47,109 --> 01:53:50,109
No matter who he is,
I will not spare him!

1914
01:53:50,984 --> 01:53:52,109
Iʼll kill him!

1915
01:53:52,567 --> 01:53:53,609
Are you done?

1916
01:53:54,817 --> 01:53:55,942
Send them out.

1917
01:53:55,942 --> 01:53:57,234
Letʼs speak in private.

1918
01:53:58,442 --> 01:54:00,609
You guys carry on.
Iʼll come later.

1919
01:54:00,817 --> 01:54:03,025
Landlord,
your crotch was superb.

1920
01:54:03,025 --> 01:54:05,400
Not his crotch you idiot.
His Scotch!

1921
01:54:09,859 --> 01:54:11,234
Devendra Suttur.

1922
01:54:11,484 --> 01:54:12,775
I'm a Landlord only for namesake.

1923
01:54:13,109 --> 01:54:15,234
But I couldnʼt serve my people.

1924
01:54:15,359 --> 01:54:16,650
Then why do I deserve
the title of a Landlord?

1925
01:54:16,692 --> 01:54:18,275
Why are you speaking
like this Landlord?

1926
01:54:18,400 --> 01:54:19,609
Whatʼs wrong with you?

1927
01:54:19,859 --> 01:54:24,109
I had a big task ahead of me
before you were released from jail.

1928
01:54:24,650 --> 01:54:27,067
Rajeeva got you released before that.
- Iʼm not following you.

1929
01:54:27,067 --> 01:54:28,192
Let me tell you this.

1930
01:54:29,067 --> 01:54:30,442
Donʼt lose control.

1931
01:54:30,484 --> 01:54:31,859
You've to listen patiently.

1932
01:54:33,442 --> 01:54:35,692
Do you know who
killed our Guruva?

1933
01:54:36,192 --> 01:54:38,359
Who?
- That son of a bi*ch DRFO!

1934
01:54:40,275 --> 01:54:41,900
He tried to stop
our Bhootha Kola.

1935
01:54:42,150 --> 01:54:44,317
When that wasnʼt possible,
he killed the performer.

1936
01:54:44,775 --> 01:54:47,859
He came in a jeep and threw the corpse
in the Demigod's performing arena.

1937
01:54:48,192 --> 01:54:50,234
Do you know how he was killed?

1938
01:54:51,192 --> 01:54:52,192
Shiva!

1939
01:54:52,609 --> 01:54:54,192
Didnʼt I tell you earlier?

1940
01:54:54,567 --> 01:54:55,984
You have to be patient.

1941
01:54:56,025 --> 01:54:59,317
Listen to me Shiva!
Donʼt act in haste. Okay?

1942
01:54:59,359 --> 01:55:00,400
Listen to me.

1943
01:55:00,400 --> 01:55:03,984
Whatever needs to be done to him,
Iʼll do it with my own hands.

1944
01:55:04,567 --> 01:55:06,817
This land will be
cleansed with his blood!

1945
01:55:08,609 --> 01:55:10,150
He killed my brother.

1946
01:55:10,859 --> 01:55:12,317
Why do you want
blood on your hands?

1947
01:55:12,692 --> 01:55:15,775
Shiva, listen to me!
Donʼt act in haste!!

1948
01:55:16,067 --> 01:55:17,067
Shiva!

1949
01:55:23,400 --> 01:55:25,984
Sudhakar, give me some water.

1950
01:55:26,359 --> 01:55:27,525
I just touched a rabid dog.

1951
01:55:33,900 --> 01:55:35,567
The tiger is off to hunt.

1952
01:55:35,817 --> 01:55:37,984
Once it finishes hunting,
lock it up in a cage.

1953
01:55:43,192 --> 01:55:46,317
Instead of killing the Forest officer,
why's he at Mahadevachari's workshop?

1954
01:55:49,900 --> 01:55:50,900
Mahadevanna..

1955
01:55:50,942 --> 01:55:53,817
Before dawn sets in,
I'll finish those who killed Guruva.

1956
01:56:07,150 --> 01:56:12,734
Darkness exists to give a
man's mind and body some peace.

1957
01:56:13,109 --> 01:56:14,567
Not to destroy it.

1958
01:56:14,609 --> 01:56:16,650
But it has been destroyed,
hasn't it Mahadevanna?

1959
01:56:17,025 --> 01:56:18,567
That son of a bi*ch DRFO!

1960
01:56:20,317 --> 01:56:21,650
Can the destroyer be spared?

1961
01:56:23,359 --> 01:56:25,150
Iʼm tugging at this for courage.
- Courage?

1962
01:56:26,400 --> 01:56:29,900
Courage comes from
the fire within you.

1963
01:56:31,150 --> 01:56:35,942
Let the fire within you
not end up burning you.

1964
01:56:39,359 --> 01:56:42,775
I donʼt know if it's your words or if
it's the stuff that is hitting me hard.

1965
01:56:44,734 --> 01:56:50,692
Your words are
passing over my head.

1966
01:56:50,692 --> 01:56:52,359
It is passing by.

1967
01:56:53,942 --> 01:56:57,317
The Landlord is taking Guruva
and is passing by in his jeep.

1968
01:56:58,567 --> 01:57:04,359
While returning,
the Landlord is passing by, all alone.

1969
01:57:06,859 --> 01:57:13,567
Later, Guruvaʼs corpse is
found in the Kola premises.

1970
01:57:14,692 --> 01:57:20,192
After which, the Landlord came
home to see Guruva's body.

1971
01:57:21,775 --> 01:57:25,692
The mystery too seems to
be passing over our head.

1972
01:57:27,817 --> 01:57:29,692
Take out the weapons!
- What's wrong with you?

1973
01:57:30,567 --> 01:57:31,567
Time to finish Shiva.

1974
01:57:33,234 --> 01:57:35,109
Letʼs at least ask Landlord.

1975
01:57:35,109 --> 01:57:37,234
By the time we do that,
Shiva will finish us off!!

1976
01:57:37,400 --> 01:57:39,650
Didnʼt you say that we shall
bite when the time comes?

1977
01:57:39,692 --> 01:57:40,692
The time has come.

1978
01:57:44,109 --> 01:57:47,192
Mohan, I only said that we'll bite.
Not kill.

1979
01:57:47,192 --> 01:57:48,192
Ay, let's go.

1980
01:58:04,192 --> 01:58:07,400
Mahadevanna, you have some customers
who want their swords sharpened.

1981
01:58:07,442 --> 01:58:08,442
Who is that?

1982
01:58:09,025 --> 01:58:10,609
That ember doesn't
burn in the dark.

1983
01:58:10,734 --> 01:58:12,109
Only this stuff will burn bright.

1984
01:58:12,109 --> 01:58:13,234
Come tomorrow.

1985
01:58:14,359 --> 01:58:16,025
But I see embers here.

1986
01:58:17,609 --> 01:58:20,525
Please come.
My sword is being sharpened too.

1987
01:58:20,692 --> 01:58:22,734
This oldie is past his prime.

1988
01:58:22,900 --> 01:58:24,442
Let me fire it up for you.

1989
01:59:02,234 --> 01:59:04,025
Donʼt fight in here.

1990
01:59:25,609 --> 01:59:27,609
There goes my workshop.

1991
01:59:28,942 --> 01:59:30,317
Iʼll get you wood
for the repairs.

1992
02:00:00,650 --> 02:00:01,692
Shiva!

1993
02:00:20,859 --> 02:00:22,067
Come to me pricks!

1994
02:00:34,609 --> 02:00:36,900
You mongrel!

1995
02:01:01,900 --> 02:01:03,859
Start the jeep!
Get in! Letʼs go.

1996
02:01:06,817 --> 02:01:08,692
You guys never listen to me!

1997
02:01:08,692 --> 02:01:09,984
Keep moving!

1998
02:01:23,484 --> 02:01:27,942
The Landlord is taking Guruva
and is passing by in his jeep.

1999
02:01:28,109 --> 02:01:31,484
They came in a jeep and threw
the corpse in the Kola premises.

2000
02:01:31,859 --> 02:01:35,400
Later, Guruvaʼs corpse is
found in the Kola premises.

2001
02:01:35,442 --> 02:01:36,942
[GURUVA WAILING]

2002
02:01:37,109 --> 02:01:39,317
Do you know who killed Guruva?

2003
02:01:39,317 --> 02:01:40,317
You!

2004
02:02:00,025 --> 02:02:02,400
Ammakka, hasn't the child slept yet?
- No.

2005
02:02:08,067 --> 02:02:09,942
Whatʼs up Shiva?
Youʼre soaking wet.

2006
02:02:11,025 --> 02:02:12,400
I'm not just wet, Landlord.

2007
02:02:12,900 --> 02:02:13,984
Iʼve been cleansed.

2008
02:02:15,942 --> 02:02:18,150
Wow! Looks like the squatters
have a lot to feast on.

2009
02:02:18,650 --> 02:02:20,400
Now that you're squatting in here too.

2010
02:02:21,025 --> 02:02:22,025
Join me.

2011
02:02:22,067 --> 02:02:23,650
Well, you walked into my house.

2012
02:02:23,859 --> 02:02:24,859
Why canʼt I?

2013
02:02:25,650 --> 02:02:27,359
Times have changed Landlord.
I can come.

2014
02:02:28,484 --> 02:02:30,400
Looks like you're here
to settle scores, right?

2015
02:02:31,984 --> 02:02:33,109
Not really!

2016
02:02:33,734 --> 02:02:35,317
We eat boiled rice and pickle.

2017
02:02:36,234 --> 02:02:37,775
Sometimes,
we can't even afford that.

2018
02:02:39,109 --> 02:02:40,692
Yet, we are satisfied
with what we have.

2019
02:02:47,442 --> 02:02:49,067
Today, Iʼm unable to
eat this fancy food.

2020
02:02:49,359 --> 02:02:50,692
It refuses to go down my throat.

2021
02:02:51,359 --> 02:02:52,734
Eat that sukka.

2022
02:02:53,025 --> 02:02:54,900
Ammakka cooked it. Itʼs tasty.

2023
02:02:54,900 --> 02:02:56,942
If one's heart is good,
everything turns out well.

2024
02:02:58,150 --> 02:02:59,817
Canʼt trust everything you say
now, can I?

2025
02:03:00,109 --> 02:03:01,484
Iʼll have to check it out myself.

2026
02:03:07,609 --> 02:03:08,609
Itʼs nice Ammakka.

2027
02:03:08,942 --> 02:03:10,984
Shiva, have some scotch.

2028
02:03:11,275 --> 02:03:12,442
Iʼve been cleansed, Landlord.

2029
02:03:13,234 --> 02:03:14,234
You have it.

2030
02:03:16,067 --> 02:03:17,692
What do you expect me to do now?

2031
02:03:17,692 --> 02:03:19,192
Havenʼt you done enough already?

2032
02:03:19,692 --> 02:03:22,025
Are you our Demigod to
give us what we want?

2033
02:03:22,900 --> 02:03:24,942
Your judgement now
lies on that land.

2034
02:03:26,067 --> 02:03:27,067
Whatʼs the time?

2035
02:03:28,359 --> 02:03:29,984
Well, looks like time
is on our side too.

2036
02:03:30,817 --> 02:03:32,025
It's twelve o' clock.

2037
02:03:34,359 --> 02:03:35,359
It's here.

2038
02:03:36,400 --> 02:03:37,400
Your time.

2039
02:03:38,359 --> 02:03:39,359
Iʼll wait for you.

2040
02:03:39,775 --> 02:03:40,775
Donʼt miss.

2041
02:03:41,484 --> 02:03:42,484
Iʼll take your leave.

2042
02:03:43,359 --> 02:03:44,400
Itʼs okay if you are late.

2043
02:03:46,359 --> 02:03:48,150
I hope you know the place.
Kaadubettu.

2044
02:03:48,567 --> 02:03:49,609
Greetings. Bye.

2045
02:05:29,734 --> 02:05:31,150
Light!

2046
02:05:32,109 --> 02:05:34,317
In light, everything is visible.

2047
02:05:35,275 --> 02:05:36,734
But this is not just light

2048
02:05:37,275 --> 02:05:38,942
It's a vision.

2049
02:05:39,650 --> 02:05:42,984
The light which will shine
on the past and the future.

2050
02:05:43,442 --> 02:05:44,692
Do you see it?

2051
02:05:48,359 --> 02:05:51,234
At least now have you people have
realised that Landlord's true colours?

2052
02:05:51,234 --> 02:05:52,317
What the hell!

2053
02:05:52,317 --> 02:05:54,734
We trusted him,
only to be brought to the streets.

2054
02:05:55,234 --> 02:05:57,025
We should have realised
the day Guruva dies.

2055
02:05:57,067 --> 02:05:58,775
When he entered our
home and shed tears.

2056
02:05:58,775 --> 02:06:01,150
Guddi tricked us into
meeting the Landlord!

2057
02:06:01,192 --> 02:06:03,734
We should take him to task!
- What meeting is this?

2058
02:06:03,775 --> 02:06:06,234
Are you not throwing us a party
for coming out of the prison?

2059
02:06:06,234 --> 02:06:08,400
The landlord is
better than you guys!

2060
02:06:08,984 --> 02:06:11,650
He threw us an amazing party!
- He is awesome!

2061
02:06:11,692 --> 02:06:13,025
What nonsense are you talking?

2062
02:06:13,067 --> 02:06:14,525
Kamala, are you high?
Why are you hitting me?

2063
02:06:14,525 --> 02:06:15,900
Why donʼt you go?

2064
02:06:17,234 --> 02:06:18,817
If I go, it'll only be
to my home town.

2065
02:06:19,484 --> 02:06:21,025
Whatʼs the use of this meeting?

2066
02:06:21,067 --> 02:06:22,692
We have lost our land anyway.

2067
02:06:23,775 --> 02:06:25,400
You can still save your land.

2068
02:06:26,484 --> 02:06:30,775
We have documents to declare
this land as reserve forest.

2069
02:06:30,942 --> 02:06:35,317
Once it is declared, both your
land and the forest will be saved.

2070
02:06:35,317 --> 02:06:37,775
If it is declared as forest,
how will it be our land to save?

2071
02:06:37,775 --> 02:06:41,692
Once the declaration happens, you
can submit a plea to the government.

2072
02:06:42,192 --> 02:06:45,567
The land will be handed over to the
registered owner from the time of the survey.

2073
02:06:45,567 --> 02:06:48,400
Our department will do the needful.

2074
02:06:48,442 --> 02:06:50,109
The landlord has done enough.

2075
02:06:50,150 --> 02:06:51,692
You please donʼt mess it up further.

2076
02:06:51,817 --> 02:06:53,025
Shut up! Scoundrel!

2077
02:06:53,984 --> 02:06:55,317
We need to stand with him.

2078
02:06:55,984 --> 02:06:58,275
We will. But what about Shiva?

2079
02:06:58,609 --> 02:07:00,442
He must be drinking at
the Landlord's house.

2080
02:07:01,525 --> 02:07:03,192
Looks like everyone
has united against us.

2081
02:07:05,275 --> 02:07:07,275
Seems like our good times
have come to an end.

2082
02:07:08,817 --> 02:07:10,692
Let me show you the reality.

2083
02:07:10,817 --> 02:07:11,984
Gather our men.

2084
02:07:13,150 --> 02:07:14,609
Who is he to decide my fate?

2085
02:07:14,984 --> 02:07:16,275
Iʼll decide his.

2086
02:07:18,442 --> 02:07:20,650
Has the house been
cleansed yet?!

2087
02:07:35,150 --> 02:07:36,442
Are you done yet?

2088
02:07:36,442 --> 02:07:38,984
Your moron landlord has
cheated us of our land!

2089
02:07:39,025 --> 02:07:40,609
It seems he listens to you.

2090
02:07:40,650 --> 02:07:44,150
Speak to him and
set things right!

2091
02:07:46,067 --> 02:07:48,109
We're talking to you.

2092
02:07:48,109 --> 02:07:49,817
Why are you acting like
you don't hear us?!

2093
02:07:50,192 --> 02:07:52,234
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

2094
02:07:52,567 --> 02:07:54,734
Thereʼs nothing
left here for us!

2095
02:07:55,359 --> 02:07:58,525
The landlord has taken
over our lands completely!

2096
02:08:01,234 --> 02:08:02,692
He didn't just take the land.

2097
02:08:03,359 --> 02:08:04,775
He took Guruva too.

2098
02:08:05,442 --> 02:08:07,192
Grab everything you
can get your hands on!

2099
02:08:07,192 --> 02:08:08,942
I will take care
of that scoundrel!

2100
02:08:14,234 --> 02:08:15,400
Why the hell are you quiet?!

2101
02:08:15,442 --> 02:08:16,442
Whatʼs wrong with you?!

2102
02:08:16,484 --> 02:08:18,692
Letʼs barge into his house and butcher him!
Come on now!

2103
02:08:21,442 --> 02:08:22,609
Nobody is going anywhere.

2104
02:08:34,859 --> 02:08:37,984
Shiva, whatʼs on your mind?

2105
02:08:49,650 --> 02:08:51,317
Let bygones be bygones.

2106
02:08:51,984 --> 02:08:52,984
I'm sorry.

2107
02:08:53,984 --> 02:08:58,817
My father always told me to pay heed to the stone in
the forest, through which the Demigod will speak.

2108
02:09:01,192 --> 02:09:02,359
I listened to it.

2109
02:09:02,609 --> 02:09:03,859
The forest spoke.

2110
02:09:06,317 --> 02:09:09,025
Maybe if I lend my ear,
I might hear the Demigod speak too.

2111
02:09:10,650 --> 02:09:14,692
Our beliefs may differ Shiva,
but we are part of the same existence.

2112
02:09:15,984 --> 02:09:18,109
If something befalls me,
will you fight for my people?

2113
02:09:28,942 --> 02:09:29,942
I think heʼs here.

2114
02:09:30,859 --> 02:09:38,859
[INDISTINCT CRIES]

2115
02:10:04,942 --> 02:10:06,234
The officer is here too.

2116
02:10:06,650 --> 02:10:10,192
Shiva!
Iʼm glad you called me here.

2117
02:10:10,692 --> 02:10:12,442
Iʼm sure everyone is
aware of the matter.

2118
02:10:12,442 --> 02:10:13,817
Thereʼs nothing left to discuss.

2119
02:10:13,817 --> 02:10:14,984
How about this?

2120
02:10:15,025 --> 02:10:18,150
Take that stone from my
land and leave this village.

2121
02:10:18,192 --> 02:10:20,359
Who the hell are you to
ask us to leave our land?!

2122
02:10:20,400 --> 02:10:22,025
I think youʼve
forgotten who I am.

2123
02:10:22,025 --> 02:10:24,400
What have you done for us
to remember you any way?

2124
02:10:24,400 --> 02:10:25,442
Of course he has.

2125
02:10:25,484 --> 02:10:27,775
He cheated us of our land.
Killed my son.

2126
02:10:27,775 --> 02:10:29,609
Cheated us and
snatched everything...

2127
02:10:29,609 --> 02:10:31,150
Shut the f**k up,
you illiterates!!

2128
02:10:31,609 --> 02:10:35,484
If you can be this arrogant on charity
land, imagine how cocky I can get!

2129
02:10:35,650 --> 02:10:38,525
Is the Forest officer's presence
giving you this newfound courage?

2130
02:10:38,567 --> 02:10:41,567
I donʼt understand what is giving
you all this courage to blabber.

2131
02:10:41,609 --> 02:10:43,984
It is said that the lamp burns
its brightest before it dies.

2132
02:10:44,275 --> 02:10:45,942
I feel the same when I see you.

2133
02:10:47,359 --> 02:10:48,359
Kumara!

2134
02:10:48,984 --> 02:10:50,609
Have you all gone deaf?!

2135
02:10:50,984 --> 02:10:52,525
Heʼs speaking about
fire burning bright.

2136
02:10:53,150 --> 02:10:54,609
Go ahead! Burn it for him.

2137
02:10:54,984 --> 02:10:56,192
Burn them all!

2138
02:11:29,192 --> 02:11:30,609
Thrash those dogs!

2139
02:13:59,525 --> 02:14:01,442
Rampanna! Did the bullet
actually bounce back?!

2140
02:14:01,484 --> 02:14:02,692
My Grandpa's gun after all!

2141
02:14:05,234 --> 02:14:06,609
Heʼs one of us, Landlord.

2142
02:14:06,650 --> 02:14:08,317
Who cares!

2143
02:14:11,400 --> 02:14:12,942
I'll teach these
imbeciles a lesson.

2144
02:14:12,984 --> 02:14:15,317
Thinks they can come
to our home and...

2145
02:14:16,025 --> 02:14:18,067
Salaam Alaikum!
- Valaikum Salaam!

2146
02:14:21,234 --> 02:14:22,234
Ya Allah!

2147
02:14:32,525 --> 02:14:33,525
Landlord, thatʼs a child.

2148
02:14:33,984 --> 02:14:34,984
Is it yours?

2149
02:14:36,775 --> 02:14:39,609
If it survives, tomorrow the child
too will claim its share of land.

2150
02:15:43,067 --> 02:15:44,317
Take sir away to safety!

2151
02:16:09,942 --> 02:16:11,109
Bulla!

2152
02:16:21,859 --> 02:16:23,400
Bulla!

2153
02:17:27,525 --> 02:17:29,192
Bulla!

2154
02:17:45,234 --> 02:17:46,234
Die.

2155
02:18:00,859 --> 02:18:02,900
Throw that mongrel over here.

2156
02:18:04,775 --> 02:18:06,609
Koragappa! Rajeeva!

2157
02:18:07,192 --> 02:18:09,609
How much more you plan to fight?

2158
02:18:16,817 --> 02:18:17,817
Step aside.

2159
02:18:17,859 --> 02:18:18,859
Hold this.

2160
02:18:19,984 --> 02:18:20,984
Bulla!

2161
02:18:21,025 --> 02:18:22,025
Aye!

2162
02:18:23,150 --> 02:18:24,525
Come back guys.
Thatʼs enough.

2163
02:18:24,525 --> 02:18:25,775
Everything's done.

2164
02:18:25,817 --> 02:18:26,859
Shiva is dead.

2165
02:18:26,859 --> 02:18:27,859
Shiva!

2166
02:18:28,067 --> 02:18:29,067
Shiva.

2167
02:18:29,109 --> 02:18:30,234
Shiva.

2168
02:18:31,192 --> 02:18:33,692
My son! What happened?!

2169
02:18:36,942 --> 02:18:38,484
Are all of your family members here?

2170
02:18:38,525 --> 02:18:40,359
Only a handful of you made
it, huh?

2171
02:18:41,400 --> 02:18:46,275
You canʼt fool me with that useless
stone the way you fooled my ancestors.

2172
02:18:48,317 --> 02:18:50,025
You have two options now.

2173
02:18:50,942 --> 02:18:53,317
Either let go of this land
or let go of your life.

2174
02:18:54,525 --> 02:18:56,734
Widows donʼt have to worry.

2175
02:18:57,400 --> 02:18:58,609
Iʼm here for you.

2176
02:19:00,025 --> 02:19:02,109
Kamala, what say?!

2177
02:19:04,942 --> 02:19:08,525
Remember, I'll be accompanied by my
Compatriot spirit, the ferocious Guliga.

2178
02:19:09,484 --> 02:19:15,400
Should you err, even if I forgive
you, Guliga won't.

2179
02:19:46,192 --> 02:19:49,734
PROTECT US LORD GULIGA!
[IN UNISON]

2180
02:20:35,234 --> 02:20:36,234
Go.

2181
02:21:18,984 --> 02:21:19,984
Lord.

2182
02:22:44,359 --> 02:22:47,275
On the land of Swami Varahamurthy,
before committing any atrocities...

2183
02:22:47,484 --> 02:22:50,900
The one who lost the right to teach
them a lesson, on this holy land...

2184
02:22:51,234 --> 02:22:53,442
Did you forget the guide, Kshetrapala?

2185
02:22:54,817 --> 02:22:56,984
My lord Panjurli might have
forgiven, but I will not.

2186
02:22:56,984 --> 02:22:58,650
The result of your deeds...

2187
02:22:58,859 --> 02:23:02,567
By offering your
blood to this soil.

2188
02:23:03,025 --> 02:23:05,400
I shall safeguard its righteousness.

2189
02:24:25,400 --> 02:24:31,484
♪ Varaha,
the Supreme among all Gods ♪

2190
02:24:31,484 --> 02:24:37,609
♪ Varaha,
the Supreme among all Gods ♪

2191
02:24:37,650 --> 02:24:40,192
♪ He who assumes the form of a Wild boar ♪

2192
02:24:40,234 --> 02:24:43,067
♪ The greatest of the Demons ♪

2193
02:24:43,609 --> 02:24:46,859
♪ With teeth as
hard as Diamond ♪

2194
02:24:46,900 --> 02:24:49,984
♪ He who protects
us like a shield ♪

2195
02:25:01,109 --> 02:25:04,150
♪ He who embodies the
essence of Shiva ♪

2196
02:25:04,150 --> 02:25:06,817
♪ The one who thrives on Earth ♪

2197
02:25:07,234 --> 02:25:13,067
♪ He who gives refuge to
those who believe in him ♪

2198
02:25:13,109 --> 02:25:19,192
♪ The one who has won the
hearts of Thousands of Gods ♪

2199
02:25:19,234 --> 02:25:27,234
♪ We now stand in front of
you, worshipping you ♪

2200
02:27:44,734 --> 02:27:46,400
Did he also disappear?
